    'index' => 'aa611',
    'body' => '> "Yes." ...on does anyone here read Dragon.

> Well then.
> I asked the question (semi-jokingly) because Dragon would seem to be
> the total antithesis of Traveller\'s attitude towards technology and
> reality.  I sometimes look through it, but usually nothing strikes
> me as interesting.  Still, I wanted to see if nyone here is quote
> "Broadminded" unquote to read something totally at odds with the
> Traveller universe.  So there.

I haven\'t read it for years, but it wasn\'t always antithetical to
Traveller.  In the early eighties, Marc Miller used to write the
occasional official Traveller article for the magazine.  Two come
to mind off-hand.  The first was a tongue-in-cheek but useable
half-page article on adding the milk bottle to the standard
equipment list, in the special Traveller section (!) of Dragon #51.
More useful, the official write-up on the Province of Luna, Terra/Sol,
for 1110 was a multi-page article in Dragon #87 that was later used
as basis for some of the information in DGP\'s write-up of the
Terran solar system in _Solomani & Aslan_.  Dragon was doing a
series on the Moon in different RPGs back then, as I recall.

But that was back when Dragon actually published a lot of useful
stuff that wasn\'t for TSR games, and before they decided that SF
was best represented by "the Marvel-phile".

  Steve Bonneville
  <bonn0015@gold.tc.umn.edu>

