    'body' => '
Yesterday, I exploded due to my frustration with dealing with these
megadeath weapons (actually, the ease that they can be created and used).

Well, today I\'d like to recieve any suggestions on how an interstellar
culture would have dealt with this fact.  What kind of defenses can be
set up to prevent airdrops of lethal viruses (the Snow Plague from the
"Renegade Legion" game still spooks me: a flu virus that kills...).

I think that many systems would have asteroid mining or use mass
drivers.  What are the safeguards to prevent millions from being held
hostage by a group of angry miners?

And I\'m sure that nasty computer viruses have been used before Virus as a
tool of war.  What are the viable defenses? (You *may* choose to ignore
this question: GDW has already published some good stuff about this
threat vector).




