> to get hungry.

    How do you capture one city?  Without knocking the army out
first?  Sort of like the way the Germans captured Stalingrad?  Or
perhaps the way they captured Leningrad?
    As to surrender, consider that the population doesn\'t do the
surrendering.  The GOVERNMENT does.  And they may be a long way
from giving up just because the people are hungry.  After all,
they KNOW you won\'t destroy them - you want their industry/economy.
That means you can\'t be too rough on them.
    Also, read "Footfall" (Niven/Pournelle) for an example of
just that kind of war (against the USA).  Note that surrender
was not seriously considered by the USA in "Footfall" just
because the transport nets were wrecked, and people were
getting hungry.  Note that in WW2, Germany\'s infrastructure
was demolished without forcing surrender.  The Germans surrendered
after pretty much all their military was destroyed and most of
their country captured...


>	Final note, never commit atrocities in territory you want to
> keep. Retribution killings for guerilla attacks are worthless.
> Don\'t get the population mad at you, any more than you have to
> anyway. The objective is to control planet, not a graveyard.

    Why?  Your plan of campaign will leave you a graveyard anyway.
And letting terrorists/guerrillas operate without reprisals is
likely to cost you both the war and the industry/economy you want.


>	Any comments people?  Working out the details is going to be a
> lot of work, but building a wargame scenario for BR and Striker
> out of this would be worthwhile, and worth publishing.

    Tell you what.  If you want to do this, I\'ll dig up one of
my old TCS players (Sansterre or New Home, hopefully), and I\'ll
referee your assault on a world defended by him.  We\'ll try this
several ways:

    1) exactly even resources.
    2) you get five times the resources he does.
    3) you have ten times the resources he does.
    4) you get same resources, plus one TL.
    5) you get five times the resources plus one TL.
    6) you get ten times the resources plus one TL.
    7) you get the same resources plus TWO TLs.
    8) you get five times the resources plus TWO TLs.
    9+) we keep on with the same pattern till you successfully extract
resources equivalent to two years production from him.

    I\'ve been considering such a game for some time now, and this
looks like a chance to learn something interesting about the Trav
universe...



