    Basically, a planetary defense against genocidal attack requires
the following things:

    1)  one of:
        a)  TL-incredibly high (say, 18 or so).
        b)  a change in the "Laws of Physics" of Trav.  Specifically,
the "Jump limit" must be raised from 100 diameters to 1000 diameters.
This will pretty much require that you abandon HePLaR and go back to 
"thruster plates" to make space travel economically viable (the 1000
diameter limit of our solar system is out near Saturn...)  This allows
one to detect incoming attacks a while before they arrive.  Like 
several days, as opposed to the two hours warning you might get if
your opponent goes about wrecking you clumsily (like Amondiage amd
Serendip Belt did against Neubayern, and Serendip Belt did NOT against
the abos on wherever-it-was...
    2)  Then, your planetary defenses must still use up MOST of your
