    It is NOT absolutely necessary, given a couple decades of
preparation.  BUT, given that you want to do it:

    The Key to the question is just how many high-pop, TLF yards are
you after?  And how many such worlds do you have to take them away with?
    Given that you can muster TWO TLF yards (high-pop), OR one TLF
yard PLUS two TLE yards (all high-pop), it will take around five years
per TLF yard (world) you want to take away.  Note that you will
probably have to take ALL of them, since the buffer state will probably
not give up just because you took one of their worlds.
    Add ten to twenty years after that to rebuild those worlds.  Note
that if you only need one yard, then you may be able to rebuild MUCH
faster - say two to five years...
    Of course, fifth columns could significantly change this.  One way 
or another.  And the tactical/strategic objectives of the buffer
state will have an overwhelming effect on the process.
