    'id' => '<199501100919.EAA09642@Mithril.MPGN.COM>',
    'index' => 'aa641',
    'topic' => 'Gov1 vs Gov2 - the real way to do it',
    'body' => 'IMEHO (...Extremely Humble...), and forgetting for the moment that people
want this gov1/gov2 war to be playable as TCS/BL/whatever conflict, might I
suggest that worrying over the exact TLs, etc. is perhaps a little too
specific...
If these two really loath each other that Gov1 is happy to walk through a
buffer state and try to maintain a war with his supply route running through
said buffer subsectors (fat chance - cut-off from the homeworlds is a
certainty), and given that Gov1 knows its TL is lower than Gov2... then only
a mad man actually tries to Blitzkrieg across such a large area of space.
If you get there fast, you\'ll surprise the enemy but your back-up fleets
will be miles behind and probably get wiped by the buffer state or Gov2
counterattack.
If you move the entire fleet at normal speed, by the time you reach Gov2,
it\'ll be waiting with every possible ship and probably have agreed a
multi-state strike with the buffer state that\'ll wipe you out.
As per usual, it\'s a case of slowing things down and biding your time. If
this stalemate has been going on for years then Gov1 ought to have done a
helluva lot of undercover stuff before it even thinks about attacking, e.g.
1. infiltrate the buffer govt to sow dissension and try to win back support
for Gov1 vs. Gov2.
2. infiltrate Gov2 governemnt to create splits, particularly between the
centre and outlying worlds (strikes, riots, racial hatred, anything they can
think of).
3. steal every known secret (military, economic, etc.) from gov2.
4. steal every known secret from the buffer gov but using even better agents
than in 3. because you can\'t afford to upset the buffer govt.
5. Incite some border clashes between the buffer worlds and gov2.
6. Find something that the buffer worlds REALLY need, e.g. a supply of super
jump drives or Sega megadrives - get their population really hooked on you
as a supplier of \'good\' things.
7. Embrace any odd religions in the buffer state or gov2. In gov2, prepare
anyu oddball group you can find as potential revolutionaries when the time
comes to attack gov2.
8. Well, you get the idea, I hope.
By the time gov1 comes to attack gov2, it ought to have made the buffer
state happy to accept the fleet passing through (add a huge bribe to govt
officials and throw in a free TL15 battleship or something). Blitzkrieg
across to gov2, simultaneously inciting every possible rioter or rebel
across the gov2 worlds. In such circumstances, attacking with a modicum of
surprise, gov1 might win without being wiped out.

BUT... that\'s all assuming gov2 isn\'t already planning the same thing which,
given they already have the buffer govt on their side, would be a lot easier
to do.

TRANSMISSION ENDS...

