    'body' => '
I\'ve been reading the thread Alvin started, and it has us very interested at
the office.  The whole "throwing rocks" question (the bio weapons aren\'t even
in the same league) is facinating as it relates to our known traveller
universe.

One idea posted was to figure out why this *doesn\'t* happen.  Since as I recall
the original scenario talked about was to be CT with the TNE system, at least
small, jump capable rocks won\'t be able to get to relativistic velocities (but
in CT, the common scout ship could be a planet killer (I\'ll have to do the math
one of these nights).

The fact that you can wreak a planet with KE weapons means that even a little
despot could threaten nasty retaiation... maybe that explains the looseness of
Imperial control.  Larger political groupings would fear retaliation in kind,
and the result would be much like the superpower supported conventional wars
we all know about from this time period.  (the notion of a TOT attack against
any large (Imp or Zho) enemy is unlikely)

I guess this also explains the constant "little" wars being fought over the span
of Imperial history.  

As an aside, someone talked about meson sites attacking the rocks tossed at them
It is interesting to note that you could attack a planetary deep meson site by
having the attaking ships close on the planet on a collision course. Shooting
