DGP had this inconsistency pointed out to them.  If I remember 
correctly they consulted with Marc Miller and came up with
the idea that by taking more time with calculations before
jump, a group of ships (convoy, battle fleet) could reduce
their relative spread to about plus or minus a half hour,
rather than a day.
  Calculation time was doubled or trebled, but was a minimal
inconvenience unless they were really pressed for time (like
under attack).

John Bogan
