    'day' => '21',
    'topic' => ' Disease from the Moon',
    'body' => 'Yes, the quarantine on the Apollo astronauts was due to fear of contamination
of Earth\'s biosphere by biota from the Moon.  Planning began in 1963, and 
included input from the Public Health Service, the Department of 
Agriculture, and the Department of the Interior.  The planning group also 
sought to prevent the contamination of the Moon by Earth biological entities.
I will be happy to provide references for those who are interested in 
further reading about this topic.

In a conversation several years ago with the official historian of the
Apollo research programs, it was pointed out to me that few scientists
took the possibility of contaminating organisms existing on the Moon
seriously.  After all, the Moon\'s surface is an environment similar to
what one would use if one wanted to kill microorganisms - alternating 
cycles of extreme heat and cold, intense hard radiation (from the Sun), 
and hard vacuum.  Although he did not include this in the official 
history, he suspected that the whole quarantine procedure was a public 
relations exercise, aimed at that segment of the population who had read 
too many science fiction novels. :-)

