    No.  If that were so, then a ship could be detected at a range of
2 parsecs by any scout ship (all the ones I designed had the best
sensors allowed).  I believe that the Referee\'s Book supersedes any-
thing in the Players Book as regards task difficulties.  Note that it
is ultimately up to the Referee to assign task difficulties, and so
the Ref may choose to make detection of incoming rocks automatic at
ranges of 2 parsecs if that\'s what he wants...


>>>>>>	Perhaps the reason MT seems to assume GG squadrons is that a emerging 
