    MT assumes GG squadrons because the people at GDW never bothered
to push the numbers through a calculator.  Neither have you, it seems.
    Travel time from Jupiter at 6Gs (average distance): 63.34 hours.
    This is how long your GG squadron will be out of the battle.
    If I jump to your home planet\'s 100 diameter limit at zero relative
velocity, I am within weapon\'s range of your planet in 1.44 hours,
assuming an "average" sized planet.  Your GG squadron will be 61.9
hours late to save anything.
    Note that the notion of GG refueling is intwined in all versions of
Trav.  It makes very little sense in ANY version of Trav.
    Economically, a merchant will lose large amounts of money by using
GG refueling.
    Militarily, using drop tanks to arrive with full tanks makes much
more sense than giving the enemy three days\' warning of your coming...
    So why go to gas giants?

    
> As to "immediate action" against KE weapons:
