"orbit".  So they won\'t stay in the positions you put them in.
    And what are the "predicted axis of attack"?  IMHO, any competent
genocidal maniac will pick his axis of attack to be AWAY from any
rocks you preposition.  *I* certainly would.  And if your sensors are
good enough to detect the incoming rock at vast distances, then my
spy ships can detect YOUR rocks at vast distances.  SO your rocks 
can\'t hide or anything, and I WILL know where to aim away from...


