Think about this...

A CA jumps insystem 50,000 AUs out, and launches 200 "fighters" that have been
automated to fly into your home world.  They accelerate at 6g for a couple of
months at which point they mass as much as an asteroid (special relativity)
because of their high (.999c) velocity.  They are tiny, and stealthy, you\'ll
never see them until they\'re far in system and it\'s too late.  If they come from
several directions you\'re really strained.  

They would be easy to kill, just spread sand, or whatever in their paths, at .9c
a dust mote would be deadly, but you would have to *see* them.

Maybe to defeat relativistic KE attacks, a system would spread a uniform cloud
of particles in a sphere at some radius from the mainworld, at least this would
afford some protection.  Friendly ships would know where gaps in the shell were.

Attacking fleets would have to come in at low velocity relative to the shell.

