	Basic concepts in Space War (Trav variation):

	1)  Strategic movement cannot be restricted in any way.

		a)  A ship travelling interstellar distances exists in
this universe only at the beginning and end of the voyage.  It
does not occupy the intervening points.
		b)  detectors (such as they are) operate at light-speed,
which is considerably slower than "the speed of Jump" (around
650 times c for a typical warship).
		c)  deep space points may be used as jump terminii.  See
Traveller Adventure, if you doubt me.

