Likewise your classic "But what about \'him\'?" example. Yes, I can well
imagine there *are* rocks out there, it\'s just no one\'s been pushed far
enough to use them. As an Imperial noble (due to my excessive dedication to
Scout Intelligence operations) I have played interplanetary politics and
there are an awful lot of threats, blackmail weapons, etc. that are created
but never get used. With regard to our \'Sir James\', we went for the \'kill
his economy\' approach rather than direct conflict. My Imperial bosses would
have cut off parts of my anatomy if I had openly used a rock or somesuch!

