    'body' => 'Mark Clark asked:
>This thread has been going on long enough to make me realize that the 
>real question is: Why doesn\'t this happen all the time in Traveller 
>Land?  Could we get your thoughts on that, please?

I believe I said something about this before, but to sum up:

1)  The bigger the rock-
    a)  The more dangerous it is, but
    b)  The more EXPENSIVE it is both in RESOURCES and TIME to prepare.

    Throw away Power Plants, Jump Drives, (possibly) Maneuver Drives,
    Computers, Defenses for the incoming Rock itself (like Anti
    Missile systems), etc.  *Most* of these will be expensive and take
    time to produce in proportion to either the MASS or the VOLUME of
    the rock.  (Computers, obviously, are the exception).  And it
    depends on the system, too.  TNE uses Mass for some things and
    Volume for others, whereas CT seems to use Volume for everything.

2)  When you WANT something, you don\'t DESTROY it.  (Unless you\'re OJ
    Simpson.)  If I want to capture your HIGH TECH, HIGH POP,
    INDUSTRIAL planet, I\'m not going to drop rocks on it and turn it
    into a LOW TECH, LOW POP, NON-INDUSTRIAL planet that becomes
    nothing more than a further economic burden on my empire.


----
Derek Smith - Logrus Development Corporation - Entropy Engineering

