    'body' => 'A.S.Lilly @ bnr.co.uk (Andy Lilly) wrote:

>COMPRESSED ROCKS
>In X167, Archie mentions a compressed asteroid in a diamond which 
>could form the basis for an anti-planet \'bullet\'. What happens if 
>this huge compressed mass (e.g. 400 million tons) gets accelerated 
>to 0.9c (or somesuch) - does relativity give it extra mass? Sufficient
