be enforced by manorial courts (the subsector duke might hear the trial of
one of his barons for immoral conduct or breaching his word not to kill
prisoners or whatever), but might also be enforced by the other nobility
simply stopping their treatment of a dishonorable noble as a noble.

Also, manorial courts, while an adjunct of the "household court," probably
have the local noble as presiding judge, even if he or she doesn\'t actually
sit for most of the cases.  On the other hand, most of these courts won\'t
see many cases, because fiefs tend to be fairly small.  Well maybe that\'s
