merrick@RT66.com (Merrick Burkhardt) writes:
Subject: Fifth Frontier War question

Howdy,
        I just dusted off my old FFW and we decided we\'d start a game up to
be played over the next few weeks.  I was reading the rules again, when I
remembered that all the BatRons for the Imperium (Zhos, too) were unstream-
lined.  But the old CT fighting ships shows all the BBs as having fuel 
scoops,
so what\'s the deal?

Has there ever been a net.fix of FFW to make it consistant with the rest of 
CT?
 ----

The reason that the majority of the Batrons in the Imperial and Zhodani 
service are unstreamlined is that they represent Battlerider Squadrons!
This is stated in either the FFW rulebook or one of JTAS 9-11.
The reason Battlerider Squadrons are unstreamlined is that the Battle 
carrier ( Fleet tender) has a dispersed structure configuration. ( check out 
the picture in either Library data A-M or N-Z ).


