    'day' => '03',
    'topic' => 'Fallen Rocks Found',
    'body' => '"My name is Yaskoydray.  I *AM* your father.  Prepare to die."

                                (apologies for the stolen joke....)

Asteroid bombardment is mentioned in at least one Traveller
adventure, _Secret of the Ancients_, as one of the many and
legion ways in which Yaskoydray killed his offspring and
their factions in the Ancient Final War.  (Among the others
were CBW, massive nuclear assault, nova-triggers (maybe a
big version of the Star Trigger), and planet-busters (one
mentioned in the text is the Niven planetbuster, basically
a three-portal circumvention teleport system with a grav 
plate, a mass to accelerate, and the system\'s velocity
regulator disabled.))

Admittedly, the asteroid bombardment could be several rocks,
but "what was attacked, was hit; what was hit, destroyed."
I get the impression that the Ancients didn\'t miss often.

The Niven planetbuster could be used in a way that would 
look a lot like the high fraction of light-speed rocks
mentioned, if the final teleport reciever couldn\'t be put
on the planet\'s surface.

Oh, and the TNE rulebook has a 300,000 year old impact 
crater with central spike on Kaggushus, which could also
be a meteor attack crater from the Ancients\' Final War,
judging by the dating.

  Steve Bonneville
  <bonn0015@gold.tc.umn.edu>

