    'year' => 1995,
    'index' => 'aa826',
    'body' => 'Steve mentioned that the formula would put the safe jump limit of Sol out to
Mars, which is non-cannonical.  Possibly, but there are already
contradictions in the Traveller canon wrt the 100 diameter limit for stars. 
The habitable zone of most giants is inside the 100-d limit, but none of the
published adventures (even the ones set in these systems) mentions this.  So,
take your pick of which \'canon\' you\'ll follow...

On that note, several years ago I designed a system with a belt that used
solar sails to push cargo out to the jump limit.  I set in in Macene
(Rhylanor/Spinward Marches) but changed the stellar type to a red giant to
make jumping about the belt impossible (it\'s _way_ inside the limit). 
Although non-canonical, the system could be easily moved.  Anyone want to see
the writeup?  (System chart, political structure, economy, encounter tables,
WBH details, etc.)
