>>At a constant velocity, the timerate aboard ship is tau. That is, while
>>one week passed on the ground, tau weeks pass onboard the ship.
>
>I don\'t think this is right. The GAMMA factor is gamma^2 = 1 / (1-v^2) .
>At a constant velocity, the time dialation is gamma. That is, while one
>week passed on the ship, gamma weeks pass on the ground.

Tau=1/gamma.  So we are both right. Tau is more useful for some things,
and is much easier to use with the caluculator dodge.

    tau^2 = 1-v^2
or
