    'topic' => 'Missiles',
    'body' => 'Someone asked about the performance of missiles.  I can\'t remember the 
standard CT capabilities, but SS3 in JTAS #21 gave the standard missile 
as 6G6, that is it could maintain upto 6 G acceleration, and do so for 
one turn (or 3 G for 2 turns, etc.) There were rules for designing 
missiles with different ratings, eg 6G18, 2G40, etc.

When I designed my Fusion rocket missile, the rating turned out to be 
10G100, ie. upto 10 G of acceleration for up to 10,000 seconds.  This 
allows my missiles to attack anything within 50,000 km in one turn, and 
have a total range (accelerating throughout) of 5,000,000 km (I think), 
although maintaining contact over that range is nigh-on impossible.  The 
Tl 7-12 missiles had the same acceleration, but were typically 10G3 to 
10G5, giving a range of 4,500 km to 12,500 km.  Of course, there is 
nothing to stop a character sending a missile out at a lower 
acceleration; even 4 G is plenty against any non-military target.

