    'index' => 'aa858',
    'topic' => ' XBOAT digest 181',
    'body' => '>>>>>	So has anyone out there toyed around with the MT sensor ranges and
	the capabilities of passive sensors?

	I\'d personaly like passive shipborne sensors to be able to detect and 
	track ships in the clear at much larger ranges.

	Instead of using a -1 DM per 25,000km hex I propose a -1 DM  for
	distant range with a further -1 DM per range band past that.  Maximum
	limit would be the range of the sensor as listed on the tables.

	Planetary based sensors should get an appropriate bonus because
	of their (possibly) large size.

	Ships wishing to avoid detection would be forced to move close to 
	massive bodies that are nutrino sources to mask themselves.  This
	would make GGs more attractive.

	This would also push out many weaponry ranges.  Missiles could be
	coasted out to engage enemy targets.  Fighters now become important
	anti-cruise missile defence for a fleet.  Hunting down passive sensor
	bouys/mines would become an important fleet task.

	Doing this could also force fleets to deploy outsystem, and GG masking
	and refueling becomes a distinct possibility.  Jumping insystem would
	be good for supprise, but would also immediatly expose the entirety
	of the fleet to planetary defences/sensors.

	Lots \'o comments wanted....

						Morgan Samuels 
