    'topic' => 'Sensors and things',
    'body' => 'Following from Morgan Samuels comments here\'s my two peneth.

The Original traveller ranges of detection at 1 light second and tracking 
to 2 light seconds, seem very short.

If these are assumed to be the ranges of the Fire Controll sensors, this 
makes a little more sense.  Hitting a Type-S at 3ls, needs a minimun 
accuracy of 0.009arc-seconds! (0.02 @ 1 light-second)


A passive sensor has effectivly an unlimited range, (and to some extent 
so does an active one).

What limits the range is how sensitive the detector is to very small 
signals.

The size of a sensor (at least say an optical one) limits the angular 
resolution of the sensor.  A 30cm mirror gives enougth resolution to 
image most stars (1arc-second). But the lvel of light is so faint you 
need 8 or 10meter mirrors to collect enought light.

But I digress...

Most ships should have suitable sensors to be able to navigate in-system, 
military and scout ships will have sensors suitable to get information 
(star-type, GG presence etc.) about a star system from say 4pc away, so 
that they can make plans, (refulling stratergy).  In any event using 
synthetic aperture techniques would greatly improve sensor performance, 
as would TL15 image processing computers!


GG Refulling (military)
On arriving in system the fleet will have fuel for power and manoeuvering 
for approx 3 weeks at best.  They will be unable to jump out of system.

It could be argued that the first priority is to refuel the fleet, so that it
can escape by jump if things get to hot, or jump in persuit of a fleeing foe.

(To deny yourself that flexibility seems IMHO great folly) A fleet cannot
carry the fuel it needs, the tankers would be huge, and have no room for any
weapons (i.e be _very_ vulnerable), then you would have to consider the
tankers disposable (@jump4).  Drop tanks would ease this, but degrade fleet
performace. 

Intelligence on enemy vessels insystem will at best be two weeks old, so 
effectivly you are jumping blind into a system.  When you arrive you\'ll 
want to assess the new situation and alter plans accordingly.

imagine
	The Zhos jump a moderate sized task force into a backwater world.  
	They emerge at 100 diameters to commence pre-landing bombardment.  
	Sitting round the world is the 8th Spinward Marches Fleet, A BatRon of 
	Tigeresses, and associted craft (engaged in a flanking manoeuver), which 
	promply smashes the Zhos, then has breakfast!
