    'body' => '> "Styopa" <liebx004@maroon.tc.umn.edu> complained about technology in 
> traveller.

The "tech difference" problem is one of the biggest gripes of the 
people I roleplay with.  I think when Traveller was originally 
designed the ease with which technology could proliferate was 
underestimated.  The rationalisations which I plan to use for running 
a campaign in the Spinward Marches are:

The region has been very recently colonised (within the last 100 
years).  As such many of the colonies are still struggling to make
themselves self-sufficient...but I assume in the long run they will
all be capable of producing the higher tech.

The Imperium has a ban on technology/information exports to the 
"native" governments in the Marches, this creates a black market in 
Imperial high tech equipment...but I assume in the long run that at 
least some of the independent systems will begin to match the Imperial 
technology (industrial espionage, research & development, copyright 
violations, etc).

I am also toying with the idea of the MegaCorporations holding 
Imperial Monopolies for such things as jump drive components, military 
armaments, etc...this reduces the number of worlds in the Imperium 
which are allowed to produce the high tech equipment.

On another tact, why does the Spinward Marches seem to be relatively 
free of Vargr?  Why did the Vargr not extensively colonise the area 
sometime before the Third Imperium began expanding into it?  I tend to 
assume large Vargr minority populations in the Coreward subsectors of 
the Marches.

Dillon
