    'id' => '<9502212301.AA15016@Newbridge.COM>',
    'subj' => 'Who lives in space?',
    'month' => '02',
    'ts-index' => '1995-02-21.aa897',
    'ts' => '1995Feb21',
    'mo' => 'Feb',
    'day' => '21',
    'date' => 'Tue, 21 Feb 95 18:01:35 EST',
    'body' => 'I was thinking about what PCs must do to kill time during a jump and it 
got me to windering...

Depending on how much time PC\'s spend planet bound, most PCs are going
to live out a lot of their life in space. A subsidised merchant that makes
20-odd jumps a year is going to require its crew to live between 40 and 60
percent of their lives in space. People onboard a navy ship will probably 
spend entire tours of duty on the ship.

Out of the entire Imperium, is this common? How many people would be doing
this sort of thing?  Do PCs have to have certain physical characteristics
that make them especially good space dwellers (eg. they don\'t vomit when
ever they end up in zero-g)? Is living on a navy ship with a crew on the
order of 30,000 people anywhere near the experience of living on 200-ton
free trader?

Basically, while the PCs aren\'t necessarily the Buzz Aldrins and Neil 
Armstrongs of the Imperium, they aren\'t the average office workers either.
Where do they fit in? What sort of attitudes do planet-bound people have
about space and "travellers"?

After a thousand years of it, I think a lot of the problems associated
with prolonged shipboard life would be solved, especially since the ships
have artifical gravity, but what problems might not be solved?

Do you think there would be the equivalent of cruise ships?
Just big ol\' ships that people take trips on, not so much to get anywhere,
but to just to hang out and relax for a while. I have these visions of
Capt. Stuebing on the Tukera Princess... how exciting and new.

Just wondering,
Ethan

Oh, remember all that debate about Vilani vs Solomani birth rates a while
back?  I was think about all those Aslan Ihatei (sp?) and wondering
if the Aslan can really keep up such a prolonged colonization effort...
