    'id' => '<Pine.3.89.9502232133.A26357-0100000@well>',
    'index' => 'aa908',
    'topic' => 'psionics & religion',
    'body' => 'Some dark thoughts about psionics and religion:

1) The psionic corollary to the Heisenberg uncertainty principle.
Suppose that the scientific laboratory environment itself is hostile to 
psionic activity.  Maybe all of those scientifically trained brains, 
whose brainwaves are influenced by their rational, cause-and-effect 
oriented training, just damp all the psionic activity.  We know already 
that psionic research in the Imperium only determined what the phenomena 
did, but did not explain the principles involved.  (MT Imperial 
Encyclopedia, p. 34)  

This suggests that the psionics institutes that were like regular labs 
would be the least effective.  Perhaps the most effective psi insts would 
be radically different, not even recognizable as "institutes."  Maybe 
they would be monasteries.

2) The Psionics Suppressions:  Was a Scapegoat Needed in 800?
Imperial intelligence found that the most spinward psi insts were funded 
by the Zhodani (Imp Encyclo p.50), and evidence of scandal was uncovered 
or fabricated (ibid.) in ways designed to turn the public against 
psionics.  The canon doesn\'t indicate any widespread economic dislocation 
or wartime losses that would indicate the need for a scapegoat to take 
the heat of public disapproval off the Emperor, as far as I know.  The 
Solomani Autonomous Region had been established in 704, at the opposite 
side of the Imperium from the most dangerous psi insts.  Were people 
blaming the Emperor for "losing the Solomani Rim"?

3) Suppressions:  Were the Institutes Too Independent?
Suppose that the psi insts were non-scientific, low-tech organizations 
that increased the power of individuals in ways that they could opt out 
of the corporatized Imperium.  The institutes would then be a threat to 
the hegemony of the non-psionic, scientific and technological elite that 
rules the Imperium, because the possibility that people could get off the 
treadmill, or have power beyond that provided by technology, would be 
seen as destabilizing.  So the psi insts were demonized as corrupt, 
retrogressive, subversive, Zhodani-controlled, secretive organizations, 
determined to make you do dirty things with your mind.  This has turned 
public opinion solidly against the institutes ever since (of course, the 
Vilani members of society already had a long standing prejudice against 
psionics (Vilani & Vargr, p. 37)).

4) The Psionic Suppressions as the Pogroms of the Imperium
So if the most effective institutes were the least like laboratories, and 
maybe were like places where psionic activity has traditionally taken 
place on earth (Tibetan monasteries come to mind, but so do Jewish 
Kabals), then the suppressions, which were impliedly quite violent, were 
organized and spontaneous attacks on a resident, probably religious, 
minority -- in plain Galinglis, a pogrom; in corporate/military speak, an 
ethnic cleansing.

I\'m not sure where I\'m going with this (my Imperium isn\'t particularly 
anti-religious, but it does try to keep disruptive religions from 
developing and becomimg problematic), but I thought I\'d share these 
thoughts, and solicit whatever comments you have.

--Glenn
