    'body' => 'I\'ve been thinking a little about fuel, gas giants and gas giant 
refueling.  I have a few preliminary ideas below,
							any comments?

The basic system has refined and unrefined fuel for sale at Starports, 
and of course fuel skimming.

The DMs given in Book 2 give a negative DM for jumps and malfunctions if
	"Using unrefined fuel and not equiped to do so"

(Missjumps - (on 13+) if navy vessel +1, if Scout +2)

Refinement
----
This is basically a very simple process,
	Break up the gas molecules (H20, CH4, NH3 etc) into ions, 
	than pass them through a basic mass-spectrometer to select 
	off the light elements you want.

	BTW. Using CH4 for each ton of H fuel you generate 6 tons
	of carbon.  Is there a market for this waste product!

Fuel constituents
----
I take refined fuel to be a suitable mix of hydrogen, deuterium, tritium.
AND helium-3.

Fussion of deuterium and tritium. produces a copious amount of high 
energy neutrons, quite a hazzard and shielding problem.  By including 
helium-3 in the fuel mix it reacts with deuterium, to give helium-4 and 
protons.

As long ago as the seventies the British Interplanetary Society proposed 
gas mining on Jupiter for helium-3 as a fussion fuel source.

	This is why Gas Giant refulling is so important.

Ship Drives
----
Basically I have two types of drive, those capable of using unrefined 
fuel, andthose that cannot.

Ships with refined fuel drives, may have fuel purification plants on 
board, but they still burn Refined fuel.

Ships like my Type-S have a form of multi-fuel drive.  They don\'t bother 
refining fuel, just shove the gas raw into the fussion chamber. 
(you\'d still get fussion reactions from the hydrogen, but also possibly 
from the heavier elements- O,C,N etc)

Malfunctions
----
Malfunctions due to unrefined fuel, could be from deposits of heavier 
elements clogging fuel injectors, or even fast-neutron dammage to the 
drive metal itself.

