    'body' => '
Glenn M. Coffin writes again:

>How will they assess risk, given communication time lags?  (Time lags 
>become shorter after the collapse, because the markets are smaller.)

Easy - after over a thousand years of relatively slow, stable growth,
they have it all worked out. Just plug in a few numbers here and there,
look at the case studies, consult a thousand years of records et voila,
you have a risk assessment.

Remember - we are now doing things that no human in history has ever
done - some of thesew things have never even been dreamed of (eg.
spray cheese in a can). But over two thousand years from now, given
a very similar culture and business environment, many things would have 
been done a lot more, like setting up a company.

