I\'m a long time lurker here, infrequent participator, but I hope to 
change that.

I have a couple of questions that are completely unrelated:
1) Did the Marches Campaign Book that GDW put out cover any new material 
or was it a rehash of older Traveller material?

2) Did DGP ever come out with The Black Duke? I don\'t remember seeing 
ANY adventures produced by DGP except in the Traveller\'s Digest.

3) What is the structure of the Julian Protectorate? I can\'t seem to 
find much info about them. How long have they been in existence? I 
remember seeing something about a Julian War. I was wondering if there 
was any official (or unofficial) source that has detailed the Julian 
Protectorate. What kind of Government do they have? What is their 
feeling toward the Imperium?

4) Are there Imperial Courts to handle Imperial Law? Where are they (or 
how often do they occur: 1 per sector?, 1 per subsector?).

5) Are the two Megatraveller computer games considered "canon"? Is the 
information provided in these games about the planets in the Spinward 
Marches the same as in Traveller?

6) Where is the Dark Nebula in Dark Nebula sector?

7) I remember seeing somewhere a mention of the Imperial Army. I didn\'t 
think the Imperial government had any armed forces besides the Navy and 
Marines. Who makes up the Imperial Army and what are it\'s duties? Is it 
the Army of Capital/Core?

8) Am I asking too many questions?

9) Terra is two parsecs from the nearest system (according to Library 
Data N-Z).  How did they skip jump-1 and go right to jump-2?

I\'ll post my other questions in the TML list, as they relate to TNE.

Thanks
Pete

P.S. - If anyone has any of the following magazines, I\'ll pay good money 
for them:

JTAS #1-5, 7-8, 10-11, 18-19, 22, or 23
Traveller Digest: 1-10, 12, 18-21
Challenge: 43-61, 63-68, 70-72
Traveller Chronicle: 1-4
Megatraveller Journal: 1-3
High Passage: Any

Thanks
