There\'s no real need to do that. Combat armour and especially battle dress is
not very available on the open market. The same goes for FGMP-15s. If these items
are quite difficult to get hold of, it might constitute an adventure in
itself finding some.

Also, FGMP-15s are illegal on most worlds, and in my games, so are battle dresses.
What reasons other than combat could there possibly be for wearing a battle
 dress in a downtown restaurant? So, if combat is illegal, so must battle
dress
es be!

These items also require special skills as Battle Dress or Energy Weapons,
whic
h are not that easy to get in character generation. If the PCs can\'t use the
ga
dgets, then what would they need them for?

The bottom line is this: It is far more satisfying for all involved, if you
mak
e up rationales for limitations, instead of just saying "you can\'t do that".
Th
is way, players will accept your decisions, and they have basis for hoping,
tha
t some day, they will get these cool items.
