I mean really - vector movement, detailed criticals, plenty of opportunity 
for character involvement without the "i rolled a 6, your character\'s dead" 
of standard traveller combat.  To paraphrase tony the tiger: "It\'s great!"

Also, in this same vein, i have a program i got off AOL about 2 years ago 
called GM.exe.  As a resource for a sci fi roleplaying game - no matter 
what system - this is really good.  I don\'t suppose anyone has an update to 
this?  (For those who are unfamiliar, one of the neater functions of ths 
program is the zooming feature.  You can go to levels of detail - NOT 
randomly generated as you zoom, but consistent through repeated tests - in 
this order, largest to smallest scale, all in VGA: Stellar map (shows stars 
