    'body' => 'Ethan Henry writes:
>Imperial/Aslan - the main problem here is those damn Ihatei constantly
>trucking across the voids and claiming land on Impy planets or claiming
>whole planets. War would be unplesant for both sides. The void make it
>difficult to expand in this region.

The problem with this is that a little number crunching and a little logic
thinking will show that the Awful Ihatei Threat is nothing of the kind. No
Aslan clan can afford to send out any ihatei fleet that could threaten an
Imperial _subsector_ fleet, let alone one backed by a few Fleet squadrons.
Only by total cooperation could they become a shadow of a menace  -  and
one of the main characteristics of the Aslans is that they can\'t cooperate
for any length of time.

>Imperial/Vargr - not a real border per se, but Vargr raiders are a 
>pain in the ass along Corridor. 

Only if every Imperial Admiral since the Vargr Pacification War has been a
total moron. You stop Vargr raiding by making the Vargr border worlds
responsible for any raiding. Then destroy their spaceports every time a
vargr raid annoys you.* Pretty soon the Vargr worlds stop catering to the
Corsairs and start hunting them down. You could do that with a lot less
than the Corridor fleet.

*Historical note: That\'s the way (at least according to Dudley Pope) the
 Buccaneers handled Spanish raids.

[Btw: Yes, I know that I\'m doing exactly what I\'ve argued against in 
 connection with other subjects. I\'m saying: "This is impossible",
 instead of saying: "This is a historical fact. How can we explain it?"
 I\'m sorry. I\'ve tried to imagine how the Aslan and the Vargr could 
 become such menaces as they are described in Megatraveller, but given
 the information we have about them it just dosen\'t make sense. The
 closest I can come is a combination of treason and gross incompetense
 on the part of an incredible number of Imperial admirals and politicians.]
 

