The big problem with the Aslans is their lack of cohesion. (Well, the
biggest... as Steve says the fact that they are collectively weaker than
the Regency dosen\'t help ;-) Given any situation where the Regency is
significanly stronger than any single Aslan clan they have a better than
even chance of playing the clans off against each other. Say that you
have an Aslan coalition that is stronger than the Regency. Each clan 
Admiral will have to keep in mind that once the Regency is defeated he will
need his forces to defend his new worlds against the other clans. So if the
Regency can smash any one clan before being overwhelmed, what clan admiral
is going to let his ships get pulped just so that another clan can get new
lands?

Then you have to remember that the Aslans can only afford to to outfit 1,8%
of each new generation for ihatei-hood (This figure is based on the
assumption that a clan will use 10% of its naval budget on ihatei ships and
