Furthermore, ihatei are equipped with obsolescent ships. That generally
means at least one tech level drop. Steve\'s suggestion about TL 16 is
sound, because even with that, the ihatei will be equipped with TL 15,
but as it is now, they are TL 13. And as Steve will tell you, each tech 
level makes ships much more effective AND cheaper. In other words, you get 
more AND better ships with higher tech level.

As for making the neighbours TL 16, you could do that, but it won\'t work for 
me. I\'ve always assumed that TL 16 was the cutting edge of the _discoveries_ 
made by anyone in Charted Space. In other words, that every TL 16 item in 
existence today (Aritfacts excepted) were proto-types (That, incidentally, 
very satisfactorily disposes of Vincennes and that Vargr world in my 
Traveller universe).


The Vargr Corsairs has the problem that pirating isn\'t profitable unless
there are a lot more merchant ships than pirates. And I\'ve always assumed
that there is a high correlation between the size of the merchant fleet 
and the potential size of the naval fleet (I say potential, because in
peaceful times the naval fleet will be much lower than it can be. But
if there are all these Corsairs mucking about then it isn\'t peaceful times,
is it?)

Corsairs thrive where the other side\'s navy isn\'t. And that most certainly
