Ahh, but wait - note I didn\'t say replace the TRAVELLER game withthe 
TABLEMASTER game.  I said replace the spacecraft rules.  (ONLY).  On the 
whole, I agree with your analysis of the Rolemaster system - 90% bosh.  
But there CAN be wheat in the chaff...
Does anyone remember the MAYDAY ship to ship rules for traveller?  Anyone?  
I loved it - true vector movement, gravity, etc.  Clearly - if looked at 
with an open mind - I think most would agree that the space combat system 
in Spacemaster was lifted almost entirely from Mayday.
Here\'s the reasons that I like the Spacemaster design system:
1) The ships use mass in Metric tonnes and volume in cubic meters.  Not 
some 13.7 cubic meter thingy.
2) The Jump engine logic is, to me, more realistic.  Jump engines drive you 
a number of lightyears per day in hyperspace.  Not a "one week trip no 
matter where you go or how big of engines you have".
3) Ship manevuer drives can go over 6gs.  You tell me that in traveller, 
where they can design g-plates to support a 60t tank, but can\'t put 
together the pieces in a starship to give it 10g acceleration? Huh?
Anyway, I love traveller.  Don\'t get me wrong.  But I have ALWAYS been 
disappointed by the starship combat system, or lack thereof.  Seriously - 
read High Guard and tell me it makes ANY sense as a combat system for any 
but 17thC Man o\' Wars.

