in
> Deneb) is 10,000,000,000 TL16 Impies, but it gives them almost a chance of
> being a real (minor) nuisance.

I think that\'s a bit drastic...

The Imperium isn\'t at _war_ with either the Vargr or Aslan, so, for the most
part, the Imperial Navy is required to respect Imperial borders. Vargr
raiders can\'t be chased back to their bases. Vargr corsairs jump out,
slap a few merchants around and head home. A little cunning, a few drop tanks
and those big old battleships can\'t do much to stop them. The Imperial 
Navy is designed to scare off major intruders and fight major battles,
not to chase penny-ante Vargr around.

As for Aslan, they\'re annoying in a long-term way. They drop several tens
of thousands of Aslan down in an uninhabitated part of an Imperial world,
which isn\'t _that_ big a deal. Until they do it to every world along the
Imperial/Aslan border. And they start taking more land. And pretty soon,
you have a lot of Aslan under Imperial rule - for now.

> >I\'d rather not choose the other alternative, and make every Imperial Nigh 
> >Naval Officer either an incompetent or a traitor...
> 
>    I hate this one too, but the only OTHER alternative is that the
> Vargr/Aslan threats are a classic example of "crisis mongering" - not a 
> significant factor, really, but blown all out of proportion by the Impy 
> Media, the Navy (bigger appropriations, etc), etc...

Vargr, maybe not. While they might not do a lot of damage in a military
sense, they can play real havoc with trade and shipping in the area.
The smaller the ship, the better. (Gee, don\'t _players_ usually have small
ships?) Not to mention that mercenaries fighting Vargr units have to worry
that the Vargr might not follow the Imperial rules of war. No more
surrender and activate the repatreation bond - you\'re going to die.
(A "bad war" as that bit of MT puts it)

As for the Aslan, yeah, it probably is crisis mongering, at least before
the Collapse. There are probably a lot of Aslan under Imperial rule and
they don\'t have any problem with it. Aren\'t there a fair number of Aslan
in the Darrian confederation that have served them in the past as
mercenaries?
Promise them a little land and those Aslan will probably fight like hell...

Ethan

(Not as big a danger as those damned Hivers though! Who gets all the fame in
TNE? The Zhos? Aslan? Droyne? NO! HIVERS! Can\'t you see it\'s a plot!)
