One might well ask Congress.  Before the "Great Massacre" of November 1994,
there were at least two Gun Control bills before the US Congress that would
also ban private ownership of body armor and night vision equipment.  The
stated reason was that "honest folk don\'t need to worry about being shot at
or seeing things in the dark, so only dishonest folk would want these
things."

On most worlds, law level needs to be strongly tempered with local
cultural attitudes.  Just because a gun or armor is legal does not
make it socially acceptable in a public gathering.  Alternatively, some
societies with a higher law level might be so bad off that the locals
would think anyone without armor to be insane, and EVERYBODY
carries some sort of weapon (legal or otherwise).

