    'topic' => ' How about the Zhodani?',
    'body' => '
<JSHiggin@aol.com> (Steve Higginbotham) wrote:
> 
>>Mr. Ranke, how would you remedy the problems of the Aslan and Vargr 
>>threats?  Increase Tech level, population, or both?  Create more unity
>>between the tribes?

The Aslan aren\'t a major threat.  The only reason they swept through 
the Trojan Reach during the Rebellion was because the sector was thinly
populated, they overran an anti-Hierate Aslan splinter state (the
Glorious Empire) and then hit Imperial areas that had had their fleets
sent to coreward according to old Frontier War mobilization plans that
didn\'t apply.  The mobilization plan assumed that the Trojan Reach
border would be quiet, as in all the Frontier Wars, and that the ships
would be needed more near the Zhodani-Vargr border.  Remember, there 
was a fair amount of upheaval in the area as Norris fleshed out the
skeletal Domain government, and communications delay meant that by the
time people realized that Aslan fleets were on the move, they had
already reached their objectives in many cases.  The Domain, given
time, can probably organize enough to re-establish control over the
lost areas if this is the case.   

The Vargr are only a low level threat, and are only a problem when the
Imperial fleets are all busy doing something else important, like saving
worlds from the psionic hordes or destroying the core worlds of the 
Imperium for Lucan.  :)  But even a low level threat can cause a heck
of a lot of damage in hit-and-run attacks.

But there are plausible reasons why the Corridor can\'t be re-opened.
Deneb doesn\'t dare spare the naval strength that it would take to do the
job from the Zhodani border just seven years after a major regional war,
especially since the main source of reinforcements in Corridor is now
missing.  The RVE is more interested in the problems of the interior
than in using its\' precious strength to open the Corridor.  And the 
formation of the RVE is another reason why Imperial Deneb might be less
than interested in reopening the long Mora--Vland route.

Alvin Plummer <alvin.plummer@sheridanc.on.ca> adds:

>O.K.: how about the Zhodani?  How many people do they have, and what\'s 
>their tech level (about 14, as far as I can make out)?  
>
>They seem to be a real threat (at least in the offical universe), and 
>some have said that the current Regency -- ooops, I mean the Domain of 
>Deneb -- only exists at their mercy.

The Domain exists at their mercy.  In the 1100s, Zhodani tech is solidly
14, with only Zhdant and maybe a world or two more at tech-15.  The
CT _Spinward Marches Campaign_ said that the Consulate has about 6000
worlds to the Imperium\'s 11000, which if the Imperium has 9000 systems
would be in about 5000 systems.  If Zhodani population densities are
similar to average Imperial (depends on how Zhodani world generation  
works) then the population of the Consulate is probably somewhere from
seven to nine trillion, as a "back of the envelope" guess.  

  Steve Bonneville
  <bonn0015@gold.tc.umn.edu>

