    'topic' => 'RE: XBOAT digest 202',
    'body' => 'I hate to disagree with an old Lotus buddy........but I found Star 
Strike (the Space Master starship combat game) to be very good.

The basic game is extremely simple and it ramps up to extreme 
complexity (momentum in 3 dimensions being the one that springs to mind).

I found it only really suitable for small engagements between the 
smaller classes of ships.  There are quite large ships involved but we 
only ever used fighters.  Fighters do have character in this - unlike 
High Guard, (IMHO of course).

With the ICE critical hit system it\'s got a lot more flavour for role 
playing a battle - and scope for fudging so that the players don\'t get 
creamed by a lucky hit.

I don\'t see how anyone can be comfortable with FF&S and not get the 
Star Strike construction rules.  They are more complex than High Guard 
granted, but they\'re not more complicated than MT, although they do 
offer more options.

Whatever about Space Master, which, like Role Master has it\'s flaws, 
Star Strike, and the ground combat Armored Assault, are very good.

The counters sucked on my copy though.  The were too bright (pink 
warships - I ask you) and they were cut badly.

Eric.


