    'index' => 'aa987',
    'body' => 'Yo,
 The way the rules read it implies that you get
paid mail duty for *any* jump you make.
 The assumptions I have behind this are that there
is an Imperial "Small Parcel Post" system. Posting via this
3rd class will send it out (and onward) on the next Imperial
Mail ship to pass through (i.e. special purpose mail ship).
The schedule for these would vary depending on the pop and
starport of the planet.
 Sending something "2nd class" will schedule it for
the next mail ship *or* a ship with a mail contract as
specified in the rule you have mentioned.
 Sending it "1st class" will send it out as freight
on the next available ship.
 In interests of efficiency any ship with a mail
contract going through will be loaded with any outstanding
2nd or 3rd class mail, particularly if it is going towards
a "sorting office" (bascially any planet on an X-boat
route). They will get 1st class stuff too if they are
going *exactly" the right way.
 The way I play it not just anyone can sign up for
mail service. You usually have to have a proven track
record of going useful places and usually a Noble sponsor.
I also play a similar "Naval Mail" variant. It pays
the same but you only get it when jumping to or from
a world with a Naval base. It is easier to get, most
shipowners with a military background and a medal generally
have no problem. It is also a good step toward getting
a commercial mail.
   Jo
PS: If I remember correctly, the Imperial Mail Service is
actually a department of the Scout Service...
