    'body' => 'Hi there

I\'ve been (sort of) following the debate on the legality of weapons & 
armour.  In my game, Battle Dress is more than just "armour which stops 
High Energy Weapons", it also provides a sealed environment, radiation 
and biochemical protection, servo assisted actions, food, water, 
sanitation, 360 degree vision, synthetic vision, multi-band 
communications, computer assist, weapon system interface, and damage 
control/diagnosis (for the suit, not the user).  The inspiration for my 
ideas is the power suit described by C. J. Cherryh, especially in 
Rimrunner.  If you look at Battle Dress this way, it is clearly an 
offensive as well as defensive system, so no problem with the illegality 
of the thing.  For lesser armour types, you might look at some 
interaction between the weapon law level and the personal freedom law 
level to decide if an armour type is legal.

