    'body' => '
OK, so now that the latest empire-crushing blow, the Virus,
has been dealt, how does it compare to the last such event,
the "Long Night".

Presumably the Long Night was a big deal, but what really happened?
(OK, I could go look this up, so don\'t quote source material back
at me. But \'everyone just stopped using starships\' seems rather
lame.) And can the effects of the Long Night still be felt in the
modern/post-modern Imperium?

For example,

The First Imperium had a high level of cultural homogenity. Vilani
culture was the rule. Minor human races had local influence, if any.

The Second Imperium was more turbulent, but still a mixture of
two distinct cultures, Vilani and Solomani. In the First and
Second Imperia, you could go between planets and not notice a huge
change in basic culture, I\'d assume. (Which is to say, you can go
between Toronto, Manchester and Taipei today and find the same 
basic culture. They don\'t eat their children, the same basic set
of laws exists, dress is largely the same, with regional differences
and influences of past local cultures. Maybe the Imperium would be 
even more uniform than this.)


BUT - during the Long Night preceding the Third Imperium, a lot of
worlds would have developed very distinct cultures, local dialects
and various unique attributes. They had a long time to do so and
a long time to let the new culture settle in. There was very little
to change them, especially considering the overall trend of 
technological stagnation, where technological change is (arguably)
the prime motivator for the pace of modern Terran change.

So - by the 1100\'s, can these regionalisms still be felt, seen, heard?

(I put this out because a lot of source material gives me the impression 
that worlds in the Imperium are quite diverse - yet some of the
discussion I\'ve seen on this list would point the Imperium in the opposite
direction - a rather homogenous place.)

Ethan

BTW, when does the official TNE timeline start? the 1200\'s? And why does
no one in Ottawa sell anything from GDW? 
