book! <whimper>"


    NOTE:  I learned about piracy the hard way, WAY back when Trav first
came out.  The very first thing we did in our first Trav game was to steal
two
ships (plus an Impy Scout one of us got as a "going out of business" 
gift), and take them across the "border" (pretty nebulous border, since
none of us knew anything about the Imperium, including the GM).  We
sold them, bought ourselves a tough ship to raid with, spent a lot of
money setting up a base, then went out to hit on the "easy merchants"...
    Fat chance!  The very first ship we hit on got ONE (1) hit on us.
We took it.  We sold it (in ruins, because we couldn\'t afford to repair
it).  We sold our base.  Then we put a second mortgage on our ship to
pay to repair it.
    Then we tried again.  This next one was easy.  We made enough to
pay off that second mortgage.  Stupidly, we tried for three.  The third
one hit us four times, doing a total of MCr100 in damage.  Our first
effective hit knocked out its power plant, so we captured it almost
intact.  It STILL didn\'t pay to repair our ship.  So we fed the character
who thought of piracy (mine, btw :-) ) into a blender, and left the
planet (and the unrepaired pirateship) behind, never to be seen again.
    We never looked back (except for a lot of jokes about the "blender
murders", of course ;-) )...


