In Traveller Cargo is shifted at Cr1000/ton per Jump.  If fuel costs are 
ignored, then the overheads are the same if you do a jump-1 or a jump-6!

Mail
====			(has probably been covered by now)
As I understand (and play) the way mail cargos, and the X-Boat service.

Mail Cargo
==========
The ship must reserve 5tons of cargo space, and carry weapons and a 
Gunner full time.  For this space and salary, the ship is paid Cr25000.  
In addition the ship must follow a set route to a set timetable.
Because of this last condition, Subsidised Merchants are most likely to 
get the contract, because they are already on such a route, and 
owned/controlled by the Goverments in the Mail Collective.

X-Boat
======
The X-Boat service carries Fax, E-mail, etc... Anything that can be 
digitised for computer storage/transmission.  These are carried by the 
X-Boats along the main routes.  For the final trip off the Xboat route, 
Type-S ships with Commo gear carry the messages.  The grear goes into the 
large area (Aft/Portside) opposite the Air/Raft Bay.

For non-digital messages, parcels, documents where the content _cannot_ 
be digitised+transmitted this way.  Again Type-S ships are used.
(due to a modification of the fuel in Book 2, my Type-S carry fuel for 2 
jump-2s and have 6 tons cargo)
They carry the 5tons physical mail, and follow the X-Boat routes.  Though 
at half the speed of the X-boats.

