isn\'t needed, mainly.  Not obsolescence (that they cannot perform their 
function). To illustrate this, I merely point to the the USN\'s major fleet 
of "mothballed" vessels.  All of these are capable of being recommissioned 
& used when needed, despite some being 40+ years old.  They are merely set 
aside as there is no current need for that vessel (modern navies mainly 
maintaining very specialized inventories of ships) - not obsolescence.
-Steve
(a different one)


