 I don\'t think you needed to go so far. Under the
(MegaTraveller) rules any fall of over 9m automatically
deals 8 damage (Destroyed x 2).

 In one of my adventures the players were landing
on a planet under a tense situation when one of the
passengers started making a nuisence of themselves
and tried to get to the bridge with two bodyguards.
They just flicked the intertial compensator (after
bybassing the overides) in that coridor.
 The ship had 2G maneuver drives and was decelerating
at that rate. The bloke only fell 3m but the rules say
[effectively] to multiply by the square of the local gravity
which put 3m at 2G to 12m. Destroyed x 2 time!
