    'topic' => ' Regency Codes',
    'body' => 'Nick Munn <nsm14@cus.cam.ac.uk> wrote:

>I\'ve got the listing of the Domain of Deneb planets\' UWPs from MT Journal 3,
>and most of it is understandable, but I\'m puzzled by a few designations.

Cn/Dn:  one little twist is that while n is tenths of population, when n is
a zero it\'s read as ten; so "D0" is a near-wholly Droyne world.

The A(number) Aslan allegiance codes indicate that the world is controlled
by one or more Aslan clans in the same Tlaukhu voting bloc.  There are ten
voting blocs made up of various coalitions of the twenty-nine Aslan clans,
ranked in order of importance from "A0" (the Yerlyaruiwo-led voting bloc)
to "A9".  "A1" I know well -- it\'s the three-member voting bloc led by clan
Khaukeairl, which a character I once played was a member of.  "A2" is clan 
Syosuis, all by their lonesome (if you can call a clan of trillions of Aslan
*lonesome*).  I don\'t have the comprehensive Tlaukhu membership list handy.
"As" can indicate either a non-Tlaukhu clan or a mix of clans, with some
possibly Tlaukhu members.  Some odd allegiance codes for clans that are
outcast from the Hierate exist, but not in the Domain after the fall of the
Glorious Empire (post-1118).

Another one you may run into is O:(hex) on a captive world, which indicates
the world that owns it.

  Steve Bonneville
  <bonn0015@gold.tc.umn.edu>

