    'body' => 'ALIENS OF THE RIM
Mark Clark <markc@brahms.udel.edu> helpfully reviewed Aliens of the Rim -
Hiver and Ithklur in x230.
Thanks Mark, I enjoyed the laugh. GDW shoots itself in the foot (again).
Clearly they haven\'t decided various parts of the story re the Hivers, etc.,
hence the way it\'s been left with several options. Perhaps a more sensible
approach would have been the "Ref\'s" section with a detachable or
photocopiable few pages of "Player" info - this latter containing the
contradictory gobbldigook and the Ref bit telling you the truth.

JUMP HIJACKERS!
Alun Moon <A.J.Moon@newcastle.ac.uk> commented, about "commandos grabbing
onto a ship before it enters jump, then drilling through the hull to get to
the innards. Assuming they coud disable the lasers (wanta shoot your own
ship??), it would give them a week to get in.":
>
