> cargo ships. I think a whole sourcebook could be written on starports.
> Hm. Maybe I should go buy a copy of TNE and write a challenge article...

There was an article written on planetfalls and starports.  It was by one of 
the Keith\'s and appeared in _Far & Away_ #1.  The two articles ran about 20 
pages all told, with lots of charts and tables.  Very interesting.

Some of the commerce ideas I have seen over the last week have been very 
interesting as well.  Especially the dirve-less cargo ships.  One could take 
it a step further and use an unmanned pod constsiting of a lanthanum grid, 
jump drive, capacitors and cargo space.  You could charge it up at a deep 
space station on shoot it out to the jump point either by tug or mass 
driver.  In addition to savings on life support, bridge, etc; it makes a 
misjump less of a loss.  Heck, with a little luck, the pod could be 
recovered in a few decades.

Probably doesn\'t make sense in general, as towing one tug with you is less 
expensive than maintaining several of them in multiple systems, but in 
highly urbanized high traffic areas, it could be a commercial advantage.

Andy St. John
andy_stjohn@nih.gov
