    'day' => '10',
    'topic' => 'Deckplan design',
    'body' => 'Does anyone besides me draw deckplans so that the vital components of 
a ship -- bridge, drives, computer, quarters, cargo, etc. -- are 
surrounded by fuel cells?  It seems from High Guard\'s many "Fuel 
-10%" hit results on the surface hits table that fuel must be used to 
absorb some damage.

So when I draw warship deckplans, I subtract the fuel tonnage and 
first draw the decks with all of the other items.  Then I determine 
how much fuel to assign to each deck to keep an approximately 
thickness of fuel from deck to deck.  With a cylindrical shape sliced 
vertically into decks, like the Azhanti High Lightning, it\'s easiest.

I\'ve never seen a commercial deckplan like this.  Do any of you draw 
deckplans in this manner?

--Glenn
aka <sudet@well.com>
