Remember, the entire ship is sitting in vacuum.

If we assume there\'s not much difference between the fatality of exposure
to vacuum versus exposure to liquid hydrogen (death in minutes vs. death
in seconds), the question them becomes:  Which is easier to detect -- a
hydrogen leak or a leak to vacuum.

There are other concerns, but I don\'t think it\'s clear-cut that fuel
leaking into the interior is any worse than the alternatives.
