    'body' => 'Tim Salisbury on 24 March noted:
"What if the maps are based on Imperial knowledge, and they know 
nothing about the forces spinward of the Aslan...."

I think that\'s expressed in the canon.  The sector system is 
described somewhere as Imperium-centric, for example.  I\'m sure that 
there are truly vast reaches for further game development and 
adventure beyond known space.

Neil Taylor on 29 March mentioned "jump message torpedos."  These are 
in Adventure 4, Leviathan.  They flagrantly violate the starship 
design rule that requires jump capable ships to displace at least 100 
tons.  I think that one of the Flandry books (by Poul Anderson) has 
hyperspace message torpedos, but they never show up again in the 
Flandry canon.  I never allow them, because they serve to destabilize 
the communication assumptions of the game, that interstellar 
communications are only as fast as ships.
