Glenn Myers in X-boat 241 said:

> I just picked up a copy of Full Thrust, a spaceship combat system
> by Jon Tuffley for Ground Zero Games. Their rules seem simple
> but I haven\'t had a chance to try them yet. Has anyone else
> experimented using this rules system with traveller?

I\'m quite a fan of Full Thrust, as it gives a fast-moving and 
exciting game. There was a short article about integrating it with 
Traveller by Mike Elliot in an issue of Ragnarok (Journal of the 
Society of Fantasy & Sci-Fi Wargamers) last summer (and he was 
talking classic Trav, X-boat subscribers should note approvingly).

One trouble though is that a  small ship in Full Thrust can get 
blown up with frightening rapidity, and if the PCs happen to be on 
board then they might be a little upset at this.

The weapons rules would need to be tinkered with, as capital ships 
in Full Thrust have many batteries of relatively small-sized 
weapons, a la Star Wars Imperial star destroyers, rather than 
being built around huge spinal mounts. 

Nick Law
