pause for five minutes or so.
 So, why haven\'t you seen this before? Well those of
us old-timers have. They may have already worked it out.
I am, of course, refering to the designs that R.S.Dean has
put out over the years. I collected them for a while and
put them out in a short and failed publishing attempt in
Dublin. They have, however, contributed greatly to my campaign.
Instead of just a few things in the back of the Imperial
Encyclopedia, my players have loads to choose from.
 Perhaps now that "R.S." has stopped producing (due
to fatal depression inflicted by The New Era) the definitive
collection can be produced? If other people can get the
immense use I have had from these it would be certainly
worth doing...
   Jo
