    'day' => '19',
    'from' => 'Jo Grant Jo_Grant.LOTUSINT@crd.lotus.com',
    'year' => 1995,
    'index' => 'ab186',
    'body' => 'Yo People,
 Just kicked off my Traveller campaign again. (Player
just came back from the States. First thing he did was ring
and ask when we could play. :-)
 Anyway, they are working up to a long merchant haul
starting from a planet know for its VR facilities (Serabi).
Desiring to work up some skills, they sought to purchase
courses of instruction. They have done this before and each
time I\'ve had to work out again how much to charge them.
This time, however, I\'ve written it down and as it might be
of greater interest, I\'m posting it here.

 The (MegaTraveller) players manual covers Character
Improvement on p41-43. They indicate that a formal training
course lasts 200 hours and costs on average 10Cr per hour
for a total of 2000Cr for a course. My basic assumption is
that through mass-production, etc, this can be cheaper. The
basic cost is 1000Cr for a VR tape (or set of tapes, depending
on TL) of a course to teach you skill level 1.
 For higher skill levels, I said to double the cost
for each level higher. I.e. x2 for skill level 2, x4 for
skill level 3, etc. Obviously higher skill levels will
be increasingly hard to find, etc.
 You still have to roll to stay determined to maintain
concentration during a course. However, you can purchase
tapes by "expert instructors" (the higher-tech ones will
tailor themselves to the pupil) which improve the roll.
The price doubles for each plus. Obviously, again, higher
quality tapes will be increasingly rare, etc.
 Lastly I throw in a market adjustment roll (plus
currency conversion) of 2D+3 x10% for the final price.
In summary:
  1000Cr Base cost of course tape for skill-1
  x2  for each skill level above 1
  x2  for each +1 on determination roll
  x2D+3 x10% market adjustment

 So, for example, one character wanted to learn 
Broker-2. Serabi being known for this sort of thing I
tell them that any skill level up to 2 and +2 determination
is generally availible. The base cost is 1000, double for
skill level 2; 2000Cr. They want +2 on determination so
that goes up to 8000Cr. I roll an 8 for market adjustment
(110%) which makes it 8800Cr. Serabi is starport-A, TL-14
so converting to Imperial Credits puts the final price
at 8360Cr.
 I assume that a character on active duty (e.g. a
Cargo Chief while ship is docked) can only study for
about 4 hours a day. A character not on active duty
(e.g. a pilot while ship is in jump) can study for
8 hours a day. They may choose to study more but they
may get a penalty on their Determination roll.
 This assumes you have the hardware already. Some
course require supplementary hardware. E.g. a pair of
grav-sticks for a skiing course (did I mention these
in an earlier article?). My players had a full RealVision
system already on their ship for passenger entertainment
so I have no rules for working out prices for hardware.
 Anyone willing to have a go?

   Jo
