I\'d just like to say thanks for these 76 patrons-style advenure seeds, I think that 
they\'re a great resource for lost and lonely (should that be looney?)  GMs.

As the list seems fairly quiet at the moment I\'ll try to stir some comment by 
asking others what they think of something that occured to me last night.

What would the Vargr think of humans keeping dogs as pets?

i mean it\'s probable that "man\'s best friend" will have followed him into space 
(after all he got there first here on Terra).  Perhaps dogs wouldn\'t be as 
common in the Villani-based Imperium but its possible that they exist as a 
hang-over from the Rule of Man isn\'t it?  At least in the GDW material I\'m aware 
of there seems to be an emphisis on cute mascot-type creatures carried abord 
starships, why not include dogs?

I know that Vargr are far removed from our household pets but imagine the sort 
of relations that any human goverment would have with a newly encountered 
alien race that kept chimpanzees for pets (making them do tricks etc)?  i\'m sur 
it would excite even stronger emotions in Vargr, as they\'re supposed to be  
impulsive, prone to racial pride and sensitive about their beginnings.

All of the above is just nonsense really but the possibilities are amusing...
"Quick hide bozo, Admiral Grvrrrghhh is about to inspect our ship!"

Please don\'t take this too seriously, 
byee
Rob
