Internet=(xboat@mpgn.com)

>What would the Vargr think of humans keeping dogs as pets?

Well, as always with the Vargr, that would depend on the
individual Vargr. I think. Some may be offended, and some
probably doesn\'t care. It\'s not even certain that a Vargr
will recognize a dog as a "predecessor" (a german
shephard probably, but what about chinese dogs?).

As mentioned in the interview with Jeramii Boden in MTJ #3,
Boden formerly had a "Terran dog". Now he owns a "gena"
- a genetically altered animal - in this case a dog. As he
mentions, this sometimes brings him into trouble with the
Vargr.

I once ran a campaign where one of the PCs were a Vargr.
They were merchants and were transporting passengers, and
one passenger was a little girl with a toy dog. She looked
at the Vargr with big surprised eyes and I had some fun
with the Vargr PC, but she (the Vargr) didn\'t do anything.

>i mean it\'s probable that "man\'s best friend" will have followed
>him into space (after all he got there first here on Terra).
>Perhaps dogs wouldn\'t be as common in the Villani-based
>Imperium but its possible that they exist as a hang-over from
>the Rule of Man isn\'t it?

What I can glean from the interview with Boden, dogs are
uncommon in the Domain of Deneb, but not more so that
the general public is aware of their existence and how they
look.

>All of the above is just nonsense really but the possibilities
>are amusing...

Yes, excactly. And that\'s what we are here for, after all.

I think that you should determine a Vargrs reaction to a pet
dog based on how you think that individual Vargr would
react (was this a tautology? :-)). In this way, you will also
get individual aliens, and not only stereotypes.

>Please don\'t take this too seriously,

I won\'t. After all, this is only a game.

<putting on my asbest-suit>

Mark Seemann
ms@oem.dk
