==================================CUT-HERE====================================

                          A T T E N T I O N !

                 T M L   P B E M   L I S T E N E R S !

There is the possibility that we will be allowing the addition of a very
few new players/PCs in the 1995 TML PBEM.  It looks like we may have one
or two current players dropping out and we (the Refs.) plan to unload
a number of NPCs (how many and who TBD) in the very near future.  These
two events will combine to leave noticable gaps in the Elissa crew
complement and, further, will reduce the administrative overhead such
that we can now manage the game with new players.

Before we do actually add any new players, we have to decide how many
we are interested in adding, and then who we will actual allow into the
game.  This is where you all come in.

One of the single most important criteria we have always used when selecting
new players is their ability to write well and communicate effectively.
This, coupled with an active imagination and a mature attitude, are the
building blocks of our concept of the perfect PBEM member.  Solid knowledge
of Traveller rules rates a distant third to these elements.

Since we can\'t sit down, face to face, and interview each of you for the
game, we\'re going to do the next best thing.  We\'re going to make you
submit resumes.  While not resumes in the classical sense, they\'ll give
us a good grip on you\'re ability to game over the network, and how you\'ll
mesh with the current players in the present game scenario.

If you\'re interested in actually participating in the TML PBEM, here\'s what
we want from each of you:

  1) A fully fleshed-out player character, built using either Classic
     Traveller or MegaTraveller rules (please specify which you used.)
     Include:
       a) Character Name, age, & profession.
       b) Character UPP (stats).
       c) Complete list of character skills.
       d) Physical description, including height, weight, hair & eye color,
          typical mode of dress, & any distinguishing characteristics.
       e) Complete career path produced while creating the character.
  2) A complete history for the character, including homeworld (must be
     some documented location in the 3rd Imperium.)
  3) A short story.  This may be the most important of the three items,
     since it will give us an idea of how well you write, plus it should
     tell us a bit about the personality of your character.  This story
     really should be *short*, and the ideal length is between one and
     two pages (60-120 lines of text).  Write about anything: a chance
     encounter in a bar, a love scene, a shipboard situation, slogging
     through a swamp, you name it.  Just make sure your PC is deeply
     involved. (A piece of advice: if past PBEM turns tell you anything,
     it\'s that you\'re more likely to be involved in conversations than
     space battles, the last 2 turns not withstanding.  Bear this in mind
     when writing your story. Also, you\'ll be better off demonstrating to
     us that you can make a relatively run-of-the-mill character interesting
     then designing the ultimate genius/spy/ninja/starship pilot.  THIS
     IS VERY IMPORTANT.  WE WANT GOOD ROLE-PLAYERS, NOT MUNCHKIN-BUILT
     POWER-CHARACTERS.)

Those are the entrance requirements.  If you\'re interested in joining the
game, we need to see the above material mailed to pbemref@engrg.uwo.ca
by no later than Friday, 17 Feb.  This doesn\'t guarantee anyone a slot in
the next turn (which starts the following Monday), but if your material
makes the cut, it could move you to the head of the waiting-line.

See you in the Wire.
