    'index' => 'ab221',
    'body' => 'Hi all,

I was just thinking. If the Vargr are really derived from dogs ala
Grandfather and all that, what genetic characteristics would they have
retained? Do they smell the same? Do they have the same pheromones, sexual
compatibility, etc. (not wishing to raise anyone\'s blood pressure, we\'ll
leave the last subject well alone).

Perhaps Vargr would hate dogs? After all, dogs are hardly renowned for their
intelligence. Their reaction on meeting a Vargr (assuming it has the same
type of smell as a dog) would surely be to go and check out the exact smell
of this new \'dog\'. We all know how dogs go about doing that...

Humans A and B return to their ship to meet Vargr V.

A: "Hi Grrrwk. Look at the beauty we managed to pick up in the pet market
today."
V: "A DOG! I\'ve told you before about..."
A: "But look at its cute eyes. It\'s a puddle, so I\'m told."
B: "No, that\'s poodle, dung-head!"
V: "I don\'t care. If it comes one step closer."
B: "He\'s just trying to tell you it likes you, Grrrwk!"
V: "I\'m warning you! What in Harak\'s name is it doing to my leg?"
A: "Aw look, it must like you"
BBBBBLLLLLAAAAMMMMMMM
A & B: (backing away) "Hey now Grrrwk, put the pistol down..."
V: (holding smoking snub pistol) "If you ever, ever, ever..."

I think I\'m going to have some fun with this one. :-)

Andy

P.S. Do you think Aslan have the same effect on cats?

