    'from' => 'Orlando',
    'body' => '>What would the Vargr think of humans keeping dogs as pets?

An interesting question, actually. The answer is likely dependent on how
much the Terran human-canine relationship will have changed in ~3000 years.

>I know that Vargr are far removed from our household pets but imagine the
sort
>of relations that any human goverment would have with a newly encountered
>alien race that kept chimpanzees for pets (making them do tricks etc)?  i\'m
>sur

I don\'t know how well know this is known to the average Traveller in the
Imperium, but it was my impression that canon dictated Ancients used Terran
dog DNA to create the Vargr - indicating that they are indeed quite
related, perhaps moreso than humans to chimps. Furthermore, I don\'t think
humans would react too strongly to other races using ape-like critters as
lab animals and dog-and-pony shows - after all, we ourselves use our
genetic co-descendents for such in this day and age.

IMHO a simple solution is to opt for the Vargr being somewhat dismayed at
humans keeping dogs for pets, but a more realistic (and ultimately more
interesting) on is to play it case by case, determining what factors into
an individual Vargr\'s reaction.

