    'body' => 'In digest 256
>Furthermore, I don\'t think
>humans would react too strongly to other races using ape-like critters as
>lab animals and dog-and-pony shows - after all, we ourselves use our
>genetic co-descendents for such in this day and age.

Yep, you\'re probably right.  However people are a strange lot and sometimes
what we do to our 
friends/relations/genetic relatives might be acceptable when we do it
ourselves but unforgivable if perpetrated 
by others.  This is true for different human societies  might it not be even
more true for ALIEN beings.. I mean 
they\'re all wrong, wrong,.... misshapen, unpredictable, probably even
downright evil (lets face it a certain 
paranoia seems a inherent in humanity).. but I\'m ranting.

lots of people said something like
>I think that it\'s up to the individual Vargr
 this is a valid point but IMHO it\'s good to come up with some
generalisations to describe the other Races, 
otherwise we have no baseline from which to create that individuality.  If
every question was answered this way 
we would be dealing with humans(dare I say in alien suits 8-) ) as we are all
indivduals too! (I think?).

Anyway i\'m happy with the thread as all I set out to do was start some
discussion :-).


Hugh Forster said:
>So I  _know_ SDBs can\'t travel fast enough to defend a system 
>from one  point, and I _know_ commo isn\'t fast enough to 
>co-ordinate a whole  system\'s battle; but all the players 
>have been living in a world where  they _could_ until MT 
>and TNE came out, and I elected to selectively  implement 
>rules rather than change the laws of physics as discerned 
>by  the players. Game continuity won out over realism.  
I don\'t know that SDBs etc are such a silly idea if you consider that only
the major world and if possible any 
Gas giants have to be protected.  In this case they just hang around in these
areas until the agressors come 
to them. This eliminates the need to co-ordinate battles over an entire
system.  I think that the battles would 
be fought over these important objectives in the system.  Thus you have all
battles occuring at the 100 
diameter zone of a planet or Gas giant.  This of course makes Gas giants
easier to defend as your opponents 
must travel longer in normal space at negligable speeds where you can detect
him and vector in defenders 
against him.  Planetoid belts may be another matter.  Actually I think the
real reason that SDBs are a joking 
matter is that they have no real military strength (you need a Meson spinal
mount for that).  They are very 
effective at discouraging small pirate ships (again assuming that the SDBs
limit their activity to the 100 
diameter zone of the primary world).
Perhaps of course all of the above is because I don\'t really hold with ships
being able to predict their vectors 
through jump etc.

Oh yeah, nice design Hugh

byee
Rob



