    'topic' => 'Alternate PC Definition',
    'body' => 'In xboat digest 241, Glenn Meyers asked about house rules which other 
gamers have developed to add diversity to their characters.

I\'ve lately been running a campaign set in the Spinward Marches during 
the Fifth Frontier War.  I\'ve done a fairly extensive biography for every 
PC and every major NPC.  For each such character, I\'ve determined at 
least the homeworld, and fleshed out the character generation by 
determining specific missions on specific worlds (let\'s see, a raid 
during your fourth term in the Navy that would\'ve been in 1100 ... um you 
were involved in a raid on Pandrin, to put down Vargr pirate bases ((not 
a real example))).  

I\'ve also determined what the character\'s family was like, and at least 
sketched out what other family members are doing, how old they are, how 
they get along with the character, etc.

Now how do I do all this, you ask?  Well, I just make it up, based on my 
judgment, the character\'s statistics and progress through the character 
generation system, and my knowledge and vision of how my universe is.  
