    'body' => '>PS you said that you had said it all before, if this is really tedious 
>please feel free to mail me a synopsis of your conclusions about 
>in-system battles, Thanks.

Rob, in answer to your attempt to understand system defences and the
new-found role of the SDB (and ignoring the unnecessarily aggressive and
sarcastic responses of other people), here\'s a short summary of previous
discussions:

(1) SDBs are, under TCS and MT (i.e. superceding CT), too small, lightly
armoured and under-armed to defend anything against anyone, apart from
shipping against small-time piracy.
(2) Hence any system defence must be by far larger cruisers, etc. or
armoured satellites.
(3) The old principle of defending the gas giant is no longer sensible
unless you have an overwhelmingly large fleet, because:
(3a) You\'re splitting your forces between 2+ spots with the obvious problem
that an equal strength enemy system will, by concentrating solely on your
main planet, immediately gain a 2:1 (or better) advantage.
(3b) Under MT and TNE rules they\'re so far apart (with regard to travel
time) that they can\'t support each other, etc. even using minijumps, etc.
(3c) Gas giants just aren\'t regarded as that important if the attacking
fleet brings in tankers, or does a short last jump in (keeping enough fuel
to jump back out) or there\'s an alternative fuel source (starport, planetary
water, etc.)

Oh, and of course:
(4) None of the above is any use if someone throws a rock at your planet at
a high fraction of the speed of light...

It took a number of people an awful lot of heated discussion to sort out the
above points (and some of them will no doubt blither on further if I haven\'t
quoted the exact points they made in my summary above). Point (4) took even
longer.

The whole reason I said:

> No, please! Not the old "SDB\'s can\'t defend a system" argument. That was
> only (finally) clubbed to death a couple of months back and then only
> because people had started on the "I can throw a rock faster at your
> planet" argument!

was not to put you off, but to stop the same amount of hot air being
regenerated on the same subject. My apologies if this somehow offended
someone but I really do wish some people would try to provide supportive
help and constructive criticism instead of stirring ashes in the hope of
sparking a flame.

If anyone on xboat _truly_ believes this list is purely for idiots running
unrealistic CT kiddy games, then perhaps they\'re subscribing to the wrong
list?

I\'m afraid the only records I have of the discussion are my own posts in
January (x167) and February (x168) which I recall supported Steve\'s
interpretation of the gas giant defence situation, and one from MSAMUELS in
February (x183). I believe the relevant flaming - sorry, discussions -
occurred in the preceding period, so xboat digests from about 160-166 might
be of help to you?

I hope this helps you Rob.

Address for flaming: A.S.Lilly@bnr.co.uk.
(Please send direct rather than wasting xboat bandwidth)

Andy

