    'from' => 'Orlando',
    'topic' => 'Vacuum Sucks',
    'body' => 'Just for cross-referencing, here\'s how GURPS deals with characters in vacuum:

The only safe way (!) is to exhale and leave your mouth open. Your body
operates on the oxygen in your blood for an amount of time based on your
Health (average man: 10 seconds). Quadruple that time if you move slowly,
or multply by if you just passively float there. Double if you
hyperventialate first, and quadruple if you used pure oxygen. Once out of
breath, you fatigue rapidly and fall unconscious (in 10 seconds for the
average character). Four minutes later you are brain dead. If rescued after
two minutes of this 4 have elapsed, you may be brain damaged.

Explosive decompression is worse, because your eardrums pop violently and
small blood vessels burst. You have to make rolls for each eye to avoid
blindness, to avoid getting the bends, and to not get the Hard of hearing
disadvantage. Furthermore, your body\'s liquids do boil into space in a
matter of hours, leaving a fragile powdery husk that cannot be used for DNA
cloning.

I\'m not to sure about the last part (boiling) passing the real-life test,
but the rest makes sense. Hey, Bowman did it in 2001. . .

