    'topic' => 'What rules to use',
    'body' => '[Andy Lily]

>>  It is up to individual referees to decide what they 
include in their games <<

A splendid philosophy, and, of course, the one on which all 
true RPGing is built. So why does this list react with such 
violent, unproductive scorn when such referees post 
ideas/rules/designs based in their own campaigns ? Not just 
me whingeing; I\'ve seen it done to others. 

Traveller is torn between the hyper realism approach and 
what is derided earlier as "kiddy" - and which is also held 
up as trying to retain the original flavour of Traveller. 
Surely, the imagination behind the adventure and the gaming 
pleasure received by the players is far, far more important 
than whether you allow SDBs to hold a planet against mighty 
fleets or insist on complex 3-D vector movement of ships, 
missiles, planets et al in every combat (I\'ve seen both 
done!). If it plays, and the assembled group enjoys, 
terriffic! Every reason for the ref to feel good about it 
and post a few ideas. And no reason for people elsewhere in 
the spectrum to flame them.

C\'mon you perishers! GDW have abandoned "real" Traveller; 
about the only creative source available is this list. At 
this rate, the cynics responsible for creating TNE will 
have been proved right.

