another minute passed

"Red Hawk Charlie" - Platoon C was in posiiton to back up the withdrawal of 
Alpha and Bravo.  Always keep a third in a good backup position thought
jedburgh 
- someone has to cover a withdrawal, and how can anyone when they are running
- 
this reminded jedburgh of the fourth golden rule "be prepared to run".   Mind

you when his platoon leaders told him "how come you never run" he responded
with 
usual aplomb "don\'t do what I do, do what I say".

All of a sudden the hairs on Jedburghs neck rose.  He heard the low phwap of
a 
laser cannon. Damn those Brimstone boys - they must think a bonus exists for 
taking the barracks - shit.

"Alpha, Bravo - execute".

He charged across the ground - 500 meters to the barracks, by now illuminated
by 
flares, and laser discharge.  He say the lead elements of Brimstone - mainly 
trucks backed up by a couple of ramshackle grav tanks.  He could hear
screams, 
occassionally blotted out as his hearing protectors cut in when a
particularly 
loud explosion cut in on his thoughts.  250 meters out, and he saw that the 
enemy were getting it together. not good.

A tac missile rippled out from the post straight into a truck.  It was
flipped 
on its side, and exploded - men, or what was left of human beings staggered
out 
aflame, like roman candles in the night.  jedburgh dropped to the ground and 
looked through the sight of his ACR, panting hard he spoke to himself "don\'t 
fail me now baby".   He looked over the barracks, and there it was - a side 
door.  well, well, well there\'s hope for human kind yet.  He motioned to the 
door, and a fireteam set off.  He and a couple of Hawks checked the
battlements 
through their scopes. Ah sentry.  He exhaled and pulled the trigger.  The
figure 
in the night jerked, convulsed and fell out of sight.  Jedburgh leapt to his 
feet and ran towards the door.  Time was against them now.

Meanwhile the Brimstone idiots were getting repaid for their stupidity in 
spades, the local boys had moved LAG troops and tac missiles to halt the
armour 
attack coming from the NW.  He looked forward and saw the fireteam stationed 
either side of the door.  Jedburgh pointed and te fireteam went to enter.  

Suddenly a flash, followed by a shock wave, knocked him off his feet. Damn,
the 
door was wired !  He looked forward through the smoke, gingerly getting to
his 
feet. Time, Time !  He ran forward - nothing was left of the fireteam save a 
rifle - typical - the weapon survives to fight another day.  He jumped
through 
the door followed by his men.  corridor. left barracks - reinforced by LAG 
troops, right stores, forward (remembering the intel report) courtyard and 
command bunker.

He directed his radioman to set up an open channel with the freshian guard 
armour brigade, a just arrived fireteam deployed to protect him.  Right
thought 
Jedburgh, lets end this fiasco right now....

his four man team ran out into the courtyard - he could see men on the roof,
and 
shilloutes scampering around, trying to salvage their defence.  Ahead was the

bunker, he saw a small sangbag defence near the steps to the enterance, and
let 
off a HE grenade from his ACR - the sudden whoomp, and light sent the sentry
to 
obivion.  His backup men ran down the stairs with satchel charges.  Jedburgh 
moved back towards a wall, 

tink, tink, tink

You bastard thought Jedburgh, no-one pops this commando on a dark night.  He 
swivelled the ACR and fired a burst which discharged his entire Mag.  He
fumbled 
around for a spare, as he saw his team run back.  Then the bunker blew, smoke

venting out from the shattered enterance.

Jedburgh switched channels on his commo link "Guard, Hawks, Objective 1
cleared"
He and his men stormed the bunker, which was a bit of an anti-climax.  A
burnt 
out shell remained, papers were all burnt, bodies mangled and warped by the 
shock wave - war was a messy business.

"Alpha, this is Bravo - fire over, locals have surrendered."

They left the bunker, the defenders were filling down off the roof into the 
courtyard where red Hawks were disarming them.

"Colonel" Havel Masterson entered the courtyard, his grav tank nudging apart
the 
enterance doors.  It juddered to a halt, the colonel jumping straight off,
and 
strode up to the red hawk command group..

"Jedburgh, my task is to coordinate prisoner transfer to the Freshians, you
are 
hereby released from your contract"

Yeah right, thought Jedburgh, here I am with some three dozen scared
conscripts, 
and you want me to turn them over to your scum. no way.

"The Freshian brigade is about three klicks away, we might as well hang on,
and 
catch a lift bac.  In the meantime we can assist in protecting the prisoners
- 
John (motioning to Bravo\'s commander) will set up a perimiter defence while
Alha 
can guard the prisoners, and you lick your wounds."

"major, do not let me pull rank on you"
"OK \'Colonel\' lets keep it simple.  Your corps is a complete joke - yur 
knowledge of tactics pathetic, and your treatment of your men zero.  I am not

letting these prisoners be left to a simple son-of-a-bitch like yourself. 
understand"

around him the red hawks got agitated, some pointing their ACR\'s not at the 
Brimstone troop leader, but there again not away from him either.  Masterson 
locked eyes with jedburgh. an eternity passed. suddenly, the comlink
crackeled 
into life - objective 1 this is guards, 1 klick away, do not engage."
masterson 
looked at Jedburgh, "this does not end here." he snarled and stormed away.

Life at the sharp end, mused jedburgh. "Harrelson, wheres those copies of the

contracts..."


