Hugh Foster:
>OK, class; what\'s the difference between a large SDB and a 
>battlerider ?

Supply.  An SDB, constructed for that purpose, could count on
its supply line and would therefore:

1) Need less space for spare parts
2) Have smaller magazines for missiles (or more batteries)
3) Could be more cramped in terms of living quarters by rotating
   crews regularly.
4) Enjoy any other benefits of an extremely short supply line.


These things would probably outperform a Battle Rider (of equal
size and TECH LEVEL) in most cases.

The difference in performance gets even more pronounced in TNE.

I am operating under the conclusions drawn in the (already beaten 
to death) thread which suggests that defending Gas Giants doesn\'t
work.

--Derek
