in a role playing game.
	I as both a player and referee tended to operate about Tech Level 10, 
thought we did travel around the Spinward Marches in our work, in order to
not 
forget the basic beauty of Traveller - space travel to distant worlds.
However, 
the problem was this - Striker appears to me to be more wargame than 
role-playing game, whereas mercenary though sadly-lacking in vehicle
generation 
rules is great in its provision of an abstract mass-combat system, which in
our 
campaign we proved time and again works....
	By being lower tech - though generally speaking still with a slight edge 
- the odd PGMP for \'stopping power\', we found a niche.  That is, firstly it
was 
easier to relate to the technology and military principles, and secondly we 
avoided excessive number-crunching by getting into situations where - we used

battledress/combat armour - they did likewise and we then proceeded because
of 
near pefect surveillance equipment to engage one another until one side broke
- 
Clauswitz\'s "friction" in motion...

Perhaps ultimately, I enjoyed that style of play - using guile to outwit 
opponents, because I had to.  I have seen players armed to the gills using 
firepower to get out of problems which otherwise might have had to have used
the 
old grey matter.  Perhaps that is my motivation behind writing the article.

regards
Jeff
"There is no substitute for victory" - Gen. Douglas McArthur.

