    'topic' => ' XBOAT digest 276  ',
    'body' => 'I do not know what other think, but I found digest 276 to be one of the best
yet 
!  I would like to take issue with a comment made by Steve of Max\'s post;

2- NATO officers were trained in the dangerous art of "fighting by the
book".
 
 Still?  I\'m sure glad that we have never quite fallen into that trap.
And that when we got close to falling into that trap, a war came along to
disabuse us of the notion.  "American Officers not only do not fight by
their \'Book\', but most have not even read it."  (attributed to some
anonymous Soviet officer back in the bad old days of the "Cold War".

An intresting ethnocentric comment there steve.  The Soviet army relied upon
the 
book, as due to poor communications they relied on knowing what their troops 
would do in given circumstances (this includes also the indoctrinal aspect).

The American army\'s bible is known as Field Manual 100-5 and to this day
exams 
are taken on the contents so that all American army officers know the
essential 
principles distilled from history by which to conduct operations.  In wartime

commanders depending upon their relationships will be expected to follow
these 
principles.  For example in the 1991 Gulf Conflict General Franks (Commander
of 
US VII Corps - armoured formation) would tell his subordinates the outline of

hisd orders i.e. `capture point x` and then require them to work out a plan
to 
support his operation, i.e. maximum lattitude to the commander on the spot.
	However, Schwartzkopf\'s relationship with Franks was such that he grew 
incensed when Franks was not advancing at the rate he wanted - i.e. no
lattitude 
to the commander on the spot.  This has some interesting connotations for 
role-playing don\'t you think....
	In summary whilst American and hopefully Traveller Mercenary commanders 
have the initiative to take advantage of weak spots in an enemies plan at a 
tactical level, and abuse them further at strategic level - remember every 
military has some kind of book from which to create a level understanding of
how 
the country, planet, imperium will fight, whether it be the latest
incarnation 
of field manual 100-5 or Imperial Marine Corps Manual 500-74..

Regards
Jeff
"Commander, tear this ship apart until you have found those plans..."

