    'body' => 'Alvin Plummer:

> In warfare, one of the major problems is actually financing all that 
> equipment.  In my own universe, I\'m planning to arrange a military 
> buildup of naval fleet\'s, and I\'d like to know how to model the problems 
> of debt and inflation in the traveller setting. (Use either the TCS rules 
> as a basis, or the Economic rules for TNE\'s World Tamer Handbook (ugh!  
> Is there anyway to make them less complex?))  How much debt can I get 
> into before inflation becomes serious... 1 times Gross World Product? 5 

    I\'m not sure that there is a relation between debt and inflation.
 Inflation,
last I looked, is an increase in the money supply relative to the overall 
economy.  If the economy grows at 5% per annum, then an increase in
the money supply of 5% per annum is not inflation.  If the economy grows
at 2% per annum, then an increase in the money supply of 5% per annum
will result in an inflation of slightly under 3%....
    Which is a real bitch t model....
    That being said, the only time I ever tried to model inflation in Trav, I
allowed
worlds to overspend their "natural" budget (as determined by
TCS/Striker/what-
ever) by any amount they chose to.  That overspending translated into 
inflation of their money supply, and a consequent devaluing of their currency
(and economy) in the following year in the amount of the overspending.
    This could be stopped by the simple expedient of stopping the
overspending,
but could not be reversed without a raterh painful period of defaltion....


> Secondary concern (To Battle Rider fans (TNE) and TCS pro\'s (Classic):

> In several of my polities (and in the Classic Imperial Universe) I have a 
> hodge-podge of ship\'s, of varying tech levels.  If I have, say, 2 TL F 
> BCr ships and 4 TL E BCr ship\'s, what is the best way to use them?

   Use the TL-F ships to do as much as possible.  The main use of the
lower TL ships will be to cover the escape of the TL-F ships if they get
in over their heads.  You _really_ want those TL-F ships to survive.


> Oh yeah: for Classic fans, this is also a good time to discuss how 
> somewhat obsolete equipment (TL E ship\'s, in the Classic Universe) is 
> best used in a TL E/F task force. 

    Same way.  TL-lower ships are generally not very combat effective,
so they won\'t allow for winning much in the way of battles, but they
can quite effectively cover retreats, pursue a defeated foe, fight 
second-rate ships (battletenders, carriers. tankers, etc).  Basically
treat them as a forlorn hope....

                                    ----Steve



