    'year' => 1995,
    'index' => 'ab362',
    'body' => '     Some months back, Glenn Goffin wrote:
     
     "A four-issue comic book series entitled Shadow Empires:  Faith 
     Conquers has the look and feel of a Traveller adventure.  Christopher 
     Moeller wrote and illustrated it, and Dark Horse Comics publishes it.  
     All four issues are published.  Organized religions with secular 
     aspirations.  Sentient worms implanted into victims\' spinal cords.  
     Grav cavalry combat.  Noble classes. Hookers.  Kusari-jitsu.  Schrager 
     Mk-I SCrew -fu.  Learned quotations -fu. Lotsa skin-tight spacesuits, 
     lots more dead bodies.  Sudet-Bob says check it out."
     
     I bought this miniseries and read it some months back.  It holds up 
     fairly well, if not for the fact that Moeller wrote a bit too 
     convoluted a story.  I was fairly convinced that Moeller _has_ played 
     Traveller before.  Trav was just a bit too prevalent.  So many things, 
     including the Grav cavalry combat, suits of battledress-like armor and 
     amazingly descriptive military unit organizations, just made me draw 
     comparisons to Traveller when I was reading it.
     
     Chris Moeller\'s beautiful fully painted pages and the Travelleresque 
     feeling make it worth your dollar.  Future Shadow Empires stories are 
     likely to follow.
     
     Dark Horse Comics usually reprints all their miniseries into trade 
     paperbacks at some point.  The price might range from between $9.95 
     and $14.95, but I can get them for 35% off with no tax (don\'tcha love 
     mail order?! <g>).  If any of you are interested in this series, let 
     me know and I\'ll notify you if and when the TPB gets printed.  
     Otherwise, I\'m sure you can find copies of the actual 4-issue 
     miniseries at your local comics shop.  
     
     In addition, if any of you want to get it for cheap, I\'ll repost this 
     message when the TPB is printed and I\'d be glad to buy copies for 
     those of you who are interested at the above discount rate, provided 
     you send me a check in advance.
     
     --Chris
