    'index' => 'ab363',
    'body' => 'Dear Folks -

In xboat 282, Peter H. Brenton wrote:

> Lasers and Particle Accelerators are supposedly heavily inhibited
> by atmosphere...

Striker and other CT sources did not allow PAWS to work in atmosphere. A
number 
of discussions covered this, with the main points being:

1.	Starship weapons use neutral particles (which hold together in vacuum 
but break up in atmosphere);
2.	Surface PAWS are charged (generally following a laser-cut "hole" in the 
atmosphere but which break up in vacuum).
(To Roger Moore: does reality agree with this old view?)

Lasers were usable in atmosphere, although their range was reduced. However,
If 
Striker I was used to create these weapons, the main problem was not the
range 
of the weapon, but the range of the sensors...

Peter did not discuss fusion/plasma weapons at all. One of my players mounted
a 
starship fusion gun weapon on a (BIG) grav tank - I have the stats at home,
but 
from memory it was a penetration of 103 and a range of 50+ km (probably more,

but limited by sensors), able to take out any tank (and most starships, at
close 
range. No wonder they were good close-in weapons in HG).

> Anyone remember the _battlefield_ meson accelerator?

I do. We used it (home ruling??) with a danger space of 10 m - ie. able to 
destroy one vehicle at a time. Much more surgical than spinal mounts.
However, 
your tank still has to be able to *see* the target - a case for drone
vehicles 
carrying sensors and meson communicators? With a meson gun, the "pop-up" 
manoeuver (dangerous at high TL\'s) is dispensed with.

- Hyphen
  (David Jaques-Watson)

