    'year' => 1995,
    'from' => 'M. Stiavelli',
    'body' => 'Steve says:
>Is it just me, or is Traveller in need of a serious reworking
>scientifically?

My answer to that is "Yes, but..". When I started playing CT in 1980-81
I was still working at my first degree in Physics. My things in travellers
looked real bad...I worked at my own Hardscience, no Thruster plates, no
Jump Drive, 3D version...Everything was similar, except the Imperium was
smaller and travelling from one star to another using Ramjets was quite
a task. Players simply did not enjoy the game. The game was not an SF RPG
any more but became a strategic wargame.
I restarted playing the old CT and later MT when it came out. I believe that:
1- the Imperium background is really great (**CENSORED** GDW for the
Rebellion and TNE..,btw I would be curious to know whether the revenues
really
went up.)
2- changing the rules in a way compatible with the Imperium history and
background is a MAJOR task. 
3- once one is through with such a task he may be tempted to publish it and
then he will get sued for copyright infringement.
Also it is unclear whether a ML is the best place to carry out such a
project,
years ago the project TDR (Traveller Done Right) on the TML did not go
very far as far as I know...
As far as I know physics, astronomy, economy, sociology, biology, computer
science (the virus...,sic), psychology are all very wimpy in Traveller...
still it is/WAS a great game!

Personally, I\'d rather develop a totally new game then try to patch
Traveller.
(and I might actually try to do it..)

                               Max

P.S. I have subjects lists for all TML materials bundles 1-646 and the new
Xboat and Traveller ML. It is computer generated and does not contain
author names. If anybody is interested I will mail them to him.

