designs, one with a meson-N spinal mount and another with increased
agility and greater endurance. In general, BF series battle-riders are
deployed in squadrons of four to six from cruiser-sized tenders (100 kton
range). [The tenders have a 30kton carrying capacity, which allows them
to carry four 7.5 kton craft, two 7.5 kton and three 5 kton, five 6 kton,
or six 5 kton craft, or a standard-sized 30kton battle-rider.] If pressed
into service as system defence craft, they will sport drop tanks or
external demountable tanks, to extend patrol duration. However, their
lack of any subsidiary craft is a distinct handicap to such employment.


