    'year' => 1995,
    'index' => 'ab384',
    'body' => 'Following Jeff\'s suggestion I\'ll start proposing something..

Draft Scenario 1
Rules: standard MT (incl. Referee\'s Companion)
Theme: two TL 14 brigades are fighting each other on a planet
X-861000-0 with a lot of rough and broken terrain. Nobody has fixed 
installations and both fleets avoid engagement. 
In order to win, one has to conquer a given, known  spot (let\'s say that 
the spot contains access to a hidden very powerful meson gun). 
Obviously it is rather artificial but it is better to start simple.
To fix ideas let\'s consider an almost  TL 8 in structure, TL 14 in equipment 
Armoured brigade fully equipped with energy weapons so as to be
less dependent on supplies...

Arm Bde on 2 Armoured btns, 1 Mechanized btn, 1 Artillery Group, 1 HQ cmp,
1 Cbt Engineers cmp, 1 Electronic Warfare cmp, 1 Logistic btn, 1 Cavalry cmp 
(on Zhodani speeders??), 1 Field Hospital cmp.

Armoured btn: 4 companies with 14 Trepida (v32) tanks, 1 HQ company
with 1 Trepida, 3 Astrin (v33) APC, 6 modified Astrin for support (equipped
also with  Recon Drones), 1 support company on 1 antitank platoon on ? 
[I\'d like something better than a FG] with 4 to 9 weapons, 1 light cavalry 
platoon on 8 (military version) Rapid Speeders. 1 airdefence platoon (to be 
defined).

Mechanized btn: 3 companies, 144 Men and 12 Astrin each. Each 12 men
squad bears 10 FGMP-14, battle dress, and gravbelt. 1 HQ company
with 9 Astrin (some modified for support), 1 heavy weapons company
with 1 antitank platoon, 1 air defence, 1 Fusion gun battery (something
heavier than the standard).  

Artillery group: 1 Meson gun battery (bulky!) on 4 MGs for heavy, long
range support, 3 medium support batteries (I would like to use MDs..
let\'s say some fusion gun here), 1 airdefence battery (on lasers
tentatively).

Cbt Engineers, EW, Logistics, etc have to be defined better.

Operations: normally the brigade will operate in combat groups depending
on needs eg armoured cbt groups (with 3 tank companies 1 mech. company,
1 medium support battery, plus minor detachments  each).

I guess that it will be possible to: 1- design much better vehicles
than the ones used here (eg the Striker Tank), 2- prove that a similar
bde with some MDs would, on the short run, be superior.

The mail is already too long, before continuing I will wait for some
comments sitting quitely while my clone gets the flames...

                               Max

