I have seen FFW, and it does sort of work this way.  The Imperials
start with a number of small Imperial Marine units.  Some of these
are Elite (which has an affect on combat) and all are to TL F
standards.  The defense forces indigenous to the worlds in the
Spinward Marches, however, are at the TL of the world on which
they are based.  These are not, however, Imperial Army units.

Most of the Imperial Army units come in as reinforcements.  And
most are at TL F.  But I believe that that\'s because of the
heavy reliance on Strategic Reserve strategy on the part of the
Imperials.  Thus the bulk of the Imperial *Army* is actually 
coming from worlds somewhere in the Interior, where TL F worlds
are, if not prevalent, at least common.

There are several non TL F Army units, however, and lots of
Colonial Forces which are brought in as reinforcements which can
be as low as (iffen I remember rightly) TL A.

