    'topic' => ' Vermin in the Pipework',
    'body' => 'On Wed, 31 May 1995 11:43:42 -0400 Andy Lilly wrote:

>Anyone subjected their players to finding an ant or wasps nest in their air
>system?
.
>"Oh God. Ah! Oooh! They sting! Damn!"
>"Get out of the suit Fred! Get out!"
>"Arrrgh! Get the bloody pressure back up! OOOOOH!"

I had a lot of fun when I threw a smaetal swarm at my players.  Smaets
were described in one of the Journal Bestiary columns.  Tiny biting
flying insect-like things with a dormant stage that can withstand
vaccuum for long durations.  It helped that they were trying escape
the planet with their lives at the time, and the swarm had every ship
being held under quarantine.  And of course it happened while they
were in the open, miles from any airtight structure.  Then they broke
quarantine and left anyway, only to find out vaccuum didn\'t kill the
suckers, and no planet would let them land because of the quarantine.

I heartily recommend them.  :-)

(The players enjoyed it too -- made for a lot of interesting action.
And Los Angeles County was spraying for medflies at the time.  :-)



