    'file' => 'XBOAT95/XBT95292.TXT',
    'id' => '<9506022141.AA23473@astro.sns.it>',
    'index' => 'ab408',
    'body' => 'I am still rather busy designing the vehicles for my TL 14 brigade using
MT rules. Just for fun I have decided to make it a heavy armoured bde
and redesign most vehicles.

All vehicles have the same basic chassis and modular components to
ease maintenance. Turret size may differ. The basic characteristics are:

Main Battlefield Tank: armor 72 and std fusion gun 79/5, top speed=720 km/h
                       (design "probably" completed)
Cavalry Tank: armor 60 and same weaponry as the MBT (the only difference
              is armor), top speed of about 2800 km/h (have to check)
Armoured Personnel Carrier: Armor 40, 1 RPA-14, crew=2, + 10 troopers
                            can operate with both the above tanks
Antitank vehicle: Armor 40 and pulse laser TL13 - 250 MW (to be designed yet)
AirDefence: armor 40, 1 RPA14 and 2 BL 47/4

Cbt engineer, EW, C3 etc vehicles will be based on the APC.

The Meson gun vehicle using the 100 ton bay and the Artillery vehicle
using a shipboard Fusion gun (500 MW) have to be designed yet.

The ideas behind these designs are:

i) the Tank should defeat everything and be ideally able to withstand
any attack. In practice armor 80 would be preferred but then to keep
the displacement to 10 tons, one would have had a sitting duck or
a ludicrously expensive thing (with the lighter grav modules).
ii) the Cavalry Tank is not too unlike the French AMX-13 or the Italian
Centauro. The can kill a good tank but would be wiped out by a bad tank..
Reco and quick actions are their tasks.
iii) the APC is supposed to resist infantry weapons (FGMP-14) and
penetrate any battledress. It carries a fully equipped squad.
iv) the antitank vehicle is based on the idea that it may be useful to
have something able to kill a tank using a low signature weapon (compared
to the fusion gun..). I am not sure it is really useful, but I like
the WWII german panzerjaeger vehicle....
v) air defence vehicles are meant to deal with various high flying 
stuff and shells. [note that all vehicles will have their own point
defence weapons]. 
vi) every few days the vehicles will have to be refuelled. Even with
more fuel there would not be room anyway for prolongued occupancy.
vii) 40 is the minimum armor (by the way if radiations are the reason
why armor 40 is required for starships, a vacuum world would have
the same requirement..).

The bde I proposed should allow one to test the relative benefits of
slow (720 km/h..) tanks versus fast tanks. Also it should be interesting
to see whether at TL14 number beats quality, that is good tanks can be
defeated by larger numbers of Intrepida tanks.

Is there interest in this stuff? at some stage I\'ll have to decide 
whether to post the designs or distribute them only to those interested..
(if any).

                               Max

P.S. Bundle 290 did not reach me and I messed up the get request (sorry).

