    'topic' => 'Jump-3, Maneuver-2 Freighters',
    'body' => 'My folkes are lookin at Jump-3, Maneuver-2, 2400t freighers
in the same class as RSDean\'s (?) "Small Bulk Freighter" from
the archives. I\'ve done out the following two ships for
comparison for them...

Pesago Express

CraftID: Pesago Express Freighter, TL15, MCr802.346
   Hull: 3688/9219, Disp=4097t, Config=4SL, Armour=40G,
         Loaded=58050, Unloaded=13480
  Power: 11/28, Fusion=3074MW, Duration=30/90
   Loco: 184/461, Maneuver=2, 148/369, Jump=3, Cruise=750kph,
         Max=1000kph, Agility=0
Sensors: EMS Active (Planetary), EMS Passive (Substellar),
         ActObjScan=Diff, ActObjPin=Diff, PassEngScan=Rout,
    Off: Hardpoints=40
    Def: +3
Control: Computer Mod3*3, 74*LargeHoloDisp, 17*HoloLink
  Accom: Crew=19 (6 bridge, 11 engineer, 2 command),
         Staterooms=19, Env=all
  Other: Fuel=901t, Cargo=2400t, Fuel Scoops, Fuel Purefier(24h)
         ObjSize=Average, EmmLevel=Moderate

    The Pesago is the low end freighter meeting a maneuver-2,
jump-3 requirement. It has an operating cost of 1212Cr per ton
per fortnight (730 if it scoops its own fuel). Although it cannot
compete on jump-1 runs, express freight contracts over a jump-3
usually give it a tidy profit margin.
    There is no surplus power for any armament. If armament is
desired a supplementary power suply must be added or else forgo
the maneuver-2 preformance.


Nakar Freight Runner

CraftID: Nakar Armed Freighter, TL15, MCr1109.008
   Hull: 3800/9501, Disp=4223t, Config=1AF, Armour=40G,
         Loaded=60124, Unloaded=15183
  Power: 43/108, Fusion=11678MW, Duration=30/90
   Loco: 190/475, Maneuver=2, 152/380, Jump=3, Cruise=2138kph,
         Max=2850kph, Agility=6
Sensors: EMS Active (Planetary), EMS Passive (Substellar),
         ActObjScan=Diff, ActObjPin=Diff, PassEngScan=Rout,
    Off: Hardpoints=+5
         Missiles X07 BLaser X09 PLaser X07
             Batt 003   Batt 003   Batt 003
             Bear 003   Bear 003   Bear 003
    Def: +15
         Sandcaster X09
               Batt 003
               Bear 003
Control: Computer Mod9*3, 94*LargeHoloDisp, 1*HoloLink
  Accom: Crew=17 (2 bridge, 3 engineer, 9 gunner, 2 command),
         Staterooms=17, Env=all
  Other: Fuel=929t, Cargo=2400t, Fuel Scoops, Fuel Purefier(24h)
         ObjSize=Average, EmmLevel=Moderate

    The Nakar is one of a class of armed freighters designed
for service on the fringe. Its jump-3 allows access to most
worlds in undeveloped areas and its maneuver-2, high agility,
and heavy armament give it a survival edge in regions not
patroled by the Navy.
    Ships of this class are seldom seen in civilised space.
The running costs are simply too high. The fortnightly costs
require a profit of 1477Cr to be made from each ton of cargo
space. Unattainable through freight contracts and very difficult
to achieve, especically for the quantities in question, for
speculation.
    However, if you assume wilderness refueling for all operations
the required profit per ton drops to 980. A very narrow margin
for freight contracts but a potential nice earner if under
subsidy from colony worlds.

