I.=09BATTLEFIELD MESON ACCELERATORS

Excerpt from Striker [Mk 1]:

"Battlefield meson accelerators are introduced at tech level 15." (page 5)

"The firing sheaf is a circle centred on the MPI (after deviation), with a
radius equal to the weapon=92s burst size...A meson accelerator may fire=20
with
less than its stated burst size; if so, the fire mission order must state
the new burst size." (page 5)

The MPI is the Mean Point of Impact; ie. the centre of the fired shot.

The stats for the TL 15 battlefield meson accelerator are:

Power:=09250 MW input
Volume:=0915 m3
Weight:=0915 tons
Price:=09MCr 10
Burst Size:=0910 cm
Crew Req=92d:=096
(Striker Book 3, page 39)

Note that Striker scale is 1 cm =3D 10 m. Therefore, 10 cm =3D 100 m radius=
;
200 m diameter. Max Stiavelli was exactly accurate in terms of danger space=
.
Next time, I=92ll look up the stats instead of going by memory!

