    'body' => 'Mark Seemann says:
>The Imperium is not a Utopia, it\'s a simulation of a real society

Well, I guess that\'s the whole point of it..

What I was just trying to say is that since it does not make much sense
for politicians to decide whether to buy Dreadnoughts or Cruisers and
then leave the strategy and tactics to the military, I would have
hoped that one of the first steps taken by Norris would have been to
put some reasonable admiral in charge of the Aslan and Vargr operations
completely free of political interference. In my universe Norris himself
supervises the Vargr front and Tranathiaf (sp?) is in charge of the
Aslan front. (not by chance this is the point where my universe and
GDW\'s started to seriously depart from each another).

Also, I am not worried by politicians saying:
"Our main priority must be to turn away Vargr and Aslan incursions, and 
