    'index' => 'ab455',
    'topic' => 'My two credits worth...  ',
    'body' => 'I have comments to make upon three postings;

1. TCS Design strategems (specifically EURISKO)
2. Nobles and Imperial Control
3. Max\'s vehicle designs

1. TCS DESIGN STRATEGEMS
I think we should do the winner of the TCS competition justice and get his 
designs published here.  Would someone please be kind enough to do the 
honours...

2. NOBLES AND IMPERIAL CONTROL
I can contribute a little to the various comments made about nobles not, or 
having limited influence upon strategy and greater influence upon the 
weapons/structures deployed to impliment the strategems.
	Regarding procurement, lets take the example of the United States (not 
to be vindictive, but as it has one of the most open bureaucratic societies
it 
yields best to analysis).  retired officers are often picked up on retainer
due 
to their special knowledge to sell systems to their former service, due to 
contacts etc.  assuming noble involvement in those companies, creates
situations 
where the procurement process can be influenced (adventure hook time)  Then 
there is the example in the 1970s where I think Lockheed was involved in a 
scandal bribing I think a member of the Netherlands Royal family to influence

procurement decisions in that state, (another good adventure hook).  Then
there 
is the problem of a noble controlling teritory with industrial capacity
reliant 
upon contracts from the military - they will seek to improve their own lot,
but 
improving that of their home industries, and so resort to "all necessary 
measures" to secure contracts, military facilities etc.  I suggest people
refer 
to Nick Kotz\'s excellent book "The wild Blue yonder: Power, Politics and the
B1 
bomber".  
	In this analysis, two bases are built to operate the craft from, one is 
in Texas, not the climate, or territory in which the bomber is expected to 
operate, or even in the performance envelope for a cold war attack on the
Soviet 
Union.  The base is built there because of the support the
Congressman/senator 
rendered the Air Force in getting the programme into reality.....  Real life
is 
often very fascinating to say the least.

3. MAX\'S VEHICLE DESIGNS
Max, enjoyed examining the designs, but without striker or MT I am a little 
stumped as to what comments I can make.  I will put together a posting 
concerning the roles and types of combat vehicles used in the future however.

> Is it really possible to combine efficiency and local political control?

