    'topic' => ' Political Control of the Military',
    'body' => 'Max writes:		
>One serious problem of the Traveller world is that the technological
>advancement has not been followed by a similar cultural and political
>development. Despite everything the world has evolved a lot in the
>last two thousand years.
<snip>
>The Rebellion, the succession by right of assassination, etc.. are very
>hard to believe in the 56th century.

I disagree with your assessment, Max; I think that developments in the
Imperium  
are pretty well supported by the history we\'ve been given. The Imperium is
the  
3rd Imperium, not the first. Culture and technology have not simply advanced;

they\'ve gone up and down. The Traveller universe is designed for diversity,  
with tech levels and cultures varying widely from one planet to the next; the

historical details support this.

Our modern belief in progress simply hasn\'t been proved true in the Traveller

universe. Things haven\'t steadily gotten better; they\'ve gotten worse, then  
better, then worse again.

While overall we seem to be doing pretty well as a planet, Bosnia proves what

we are still capable of. Hitler and Mussolini aren\'t that far in the past,
and  
atrocities occur all the time. We live on an interdependent and
interconnected  
planet; Imperial cultures are far apart in time and space, and there aren\'t  
good communications to help public opinion along. The Imperium\'s time scale  
provides hundreds of years for some cultures to develop beastly attributes,
and  
their scattered planets provide plenty of isolation to practice them in.

That said, I think you should set up your universe however you like. I just  
don\'t believe that we as a race are inevitably getting "better" all the time.
I  
think progress in the area of societal values is something hard-fought that  
could easily be lost.

--Aaron
