    'body' => 'WARNING: LONG POSTING

The aim of this posting is to firstly summarise Max\'s dilligent postings of 
designs for combat craft of the future which would be employed by a Tech
Level 
14 Imperial Marine, as a form of high-tech testbed for future warfare a\'la 
Traveller.  
	Having summarised the designs I intend to comment upon the roles of 
these vehicles (with the odd dissagreement Max) and then propose two forms of

organising the brigade (to test or argue over generally).  I have no access
at 
present to either Striker, Striker II or JTAS issue 12:Striker special so
please 
do not harass me by saying "Striker says x or y" the following nightmare 
(excluding Maxis designs) is entirely my own responsibility.  By the way, a
text 
you may want to check out for general military information for novices is
J.F. 
Dunnigan\'s How to Make War, 3rd Edition (Quill) ISBN 0-0-688-12157-8 (By the
way 
I am not on commission for the chap !)

MAX\'S DESIGNS FOR THE IRIDIUM BRIGADE

Under Max\'s Modular Combat Vehicle System (MCVS) the craft all have the same
key 
features (further details in Digests 300 +):

* Same Power Plant, Grav Thrust, Sensors, Commo, Decoy launchers, Environment
* All have no EMM Level

TYPES OF VEHICLES AND ACRONYMS

MBGT - Main Battle Grav Tank (modern day equivalent: M1A2 Abrams (US), 
Challenger 2 (UK), Leopard II (Germany), Le Clerc (France)

IFV (APC) - Infantry Fighting Vehicle (modern day equivalent: M2 Bradley
(US), 
Warrior (UK), Marder (Germany), BMP-3 (Russia), AMX (France)

CGT - Cavalry Grav Tank (Modern day equivalents: M3 Bradley (US), Scorpion, 
Scimatar (UK))

HKV - Hunter Killer Vehicle (mobile anti-tank missile launchers etc.)

ADV - Air Defence Vehicle (modern day equivalents: ZSU-23-4 (Russia), M113 
Vulcan (USA), Chapparal (US), Mobile Rapier (UK))

FIST - heavy FIre SupporT vehicle (modern day equivalents (indirect fire):
M109 
Paladin (US))

RCEW - Reconnaisance/Communications/Electronic Warfare Vehicle.  Max I have a

problem with this design, as all vehicles have EMM jammers as standard, and
good 
sensor setups, with the Cavalry grav Tanks as scouts, what use are these ?
As 
all your designs have no EMM, they cannot even be justified as being
stealthy, 
and they only serve to complicate maintenance - Max I would like your (plus
any 
other XBoaters) opinions

CSV - Combat Support vehicle (modern day equivalent: various vehicles based
on 
MBT chassis).  Nice one Max - you have a handle on combat support and those 
other jolly force multipliers most folk forget...

MGB - Meson Gun Boat
 
DESIGN VARIATIONS

MBGT - 10 Ton vehicle, 72G Armour, Main Gun FZ14, RPA14 * 2 point defence
guns.
IFV  - 10 Ton vehicle, 40G Armour, RPA14 * 2 point defence guns.
HKV  - 20 Ton vehicle, 40G Armour, Main Gun 250Mw Pulse Laser, RPA14 * 2
guns.
ADV  - 10 Ton vehicle, 40G Armour, Main Gun 25Mw Beam Laser, RPA14 * 3 guns.
FIST - 20 Ton vehicle, 40G Armour, Main Gun 500Mw fusion, RPA14 * 1 gun.
RCEW - 10 Ton vehicle, 40G Armour, RPA14 * 2 point defence guns.
CSV  - 20 Ton vehicle, 40G Armour, RPA14 * 2 point defence guns.
C3I  - HQ variant of CSV above. identical for purpose of this posting.
MGB  - 1400 Ton hull,  40G Armour, Main Gun Meson Gun fac 5, RPA14 * 10, Beam
	Laser 25Mw * 10

IRIDIUM BRIGADE - ORGANISATION (ALPHA VERSION)

structure: The brigade is broken up into battalions, which in turn are
organised 
into companies, platoons, squads and fireteams.  The Iridium brigade is 2,500

personnel in strength broken down as follows;

1st battalion, Iridium Brigade (Armoured) Comprises 6 Lances of 5 MBGTs
2nd battalion, Iridium Brigade (Infantry) 400 Troopers in 40 IFVs
3rd battalion, Iridium Brigade (Infantry) 400 Troopers in 40 IFVs

Brigade Headquarters	
Brigade Artillery
Brigade Reconnaisance
Combat Engineer/Support elements
