    'index' => 'ab470',
    'topic' => 'Iridium brigade !!',
    'body' => 'Thanks to Jeffrey for his summary and the iridium brigade order of 
battle, i still have to look into it in more detail (we might merge our 
bdes perhaps). 

Jeffrey is questioning the role of the RCEV vehicle. In my view this was 
actually covering three different roles:

Commo Veh. using two drones yet to be designed. Since commo will mostly be
via direct lineof sight beams, efficient commo in broken terrain etc requires
relay stations. These are provided by the drones deployed by this vechile.

Reco Veh. theidea is to use the drone for reco missions that might 
otherwise be dangerous. 

EW Veh. this  was intended to provide through the use of its drone/s either
Jamming capabilities without risking the cbt vehicles themselves or passive
surveillance of the opponents emissions (either intentional = jamming) or 
unintentional, acting therefore as an electronic intelligence gatherer.

Unfortunately I have not yet designed this drones..

    Cheers,
        Max



----
Massimo Stiavelli 
mstiavel@astro.sns.it
Aspen Physics Center (this week)



