I can do this.  I have my copy [relatively] handy.  Last time I
messed around with it I had all the counters.


>> Also, anyone know why some of the BatRons\' jump number increases 
>> when they take a step loss? 

> Because some of the BatRons are composed of a mixture of ships of
> different classes (and presumably, tech levels).  The assumption 
> seems to be that the obsolescent ships (with lower performance) 
> will be destroyed first, leaving the remainder to perform at the
> higher jump number.

That\'s one interpretation.  I have another.  Battle Riders.  A
tender carrying only half of its Battle Riders can jump farther
than one fully loaded.  If the counters you are referring to
are BatRon counters, then the particular BatRons could be made up
of classes of ships where the displacement ratio of Battle Riders
to their Tenders is relatively high; high enough to make a
difference in jump performance of the Tender if half of its Riders
are lost.


