    'topic' => 'FFW Counters - And the verdict is...',
    'body' => 'Erich Schneider  erich@bush.cs.tamu.edu asked about his missing
FFW counters.

>First: The Zho OOB says there are 7 named and 9 numbered colonial
>squadrons, and 8 named and 8 numbered colonial troops. My copy of the
>game has an errata slip (dated 1 Sep 81) saying this OOB is in error,
>that there are actually 7/9 troops and 8/8 squadrons. My copy of the
>game has 7 named and 9 numbered colonial squadrons, and 7 named and 8
>numbered colonial troops. I thus think I\'m missing a colonial troop of
>some kind, but I\'m not sure if it\'s a named one or a numbered one.
>Zho colonial troops in my copy:
>Esalin (20-8 MI), Sheyou (10-10 LI), Clan (10-10 GT), Cipango (1c-12
>LC), Chwistyoch (10-10 LI), Cronor (1c-13 LMi), Atsa (2-10 GT)
>476 (20-13 LI), 509 (10-12 LI), 46 (2-13 LJ), 98 (20-13 LI), 
>3112 (2-11 LI), 1067 (2-10 GT), 397 (20-13 LC), 840 (20-13 GT)
>(L is "lift", G "grav", M "motorized", I "infantry", C "cavalry", T
>"tank", Mi "mech infantry", J "jump")

There are really 7 named and 9 numbered Zho Colonial Troops and
7 named and 9 numbered Colonial squadrons.  So both the OOB AND
the errata are incorrect.

You are missing 1 numbered Zho Colonial Troop Counter.  It is
a Factor 20, Tech Level 14, ARMORED Lift/Grav CAVALRY unit.  Its
unit number is 998.



>Second: The Imperial OOB implies there are 34 Imperial BatRons and 32
>Imperial CruRons. My copy of the game has 30 BatRons and 25 CruRons. 

Similar problem.  The actual number of Imperial BatRons is 32
(what the OOB says are available as REINFORCEMENTS and) and the
actual number of Imperial CruRons is 26 (what the OOB says are
available as REINFORCEMENTS).

One of two things should be done, either:

1)  Change the Imperial OOB (Discretionary Placement section) to
read that regular Imperial forces available for initial placement
may be placed in the Imperial reinforcements boxes instead of on
the map if desired, or

2)  Change what it lists as being available as Imperial
reinforcements to read that 30 BatRons and 20 CruRons are available
as reinforcements.

The good news is that you are missing only 2 BatRons and 1 CruRon.

BatRons:

 8-0-4(4) / 4-0-2(4) Unstreamlined, # 501
 3-1-7(4) / 1-1-4(4) Partially Streamlined, # 493

CruRon:

 3-4-6(3) / 1-2-3(2) Streamlined, # 356


Good Luck,

