    'body' => 'David P. Summers writes:
>>Andory and Candory (don\'t remember the hex locations).
> 
>Thanks, I found them.  I assume they are interdicted by the Scouts
>to protect the local culture?
 
That Andor and Candory. Andor was spelled with a y in one of the earliest
publications, but all (most?) other sources leave it out. No official
explanation for the interdict has been published, but note the curious 
fact that they have functioning starports despite being interdicted.
Also I think we\'ve seen Droyne ships (in _Merchant Prince_?) that are
registered to Andor mucking about the Marches.

In my universe the Droyne of Andor developed Jump-1 drive and colonized 
Candory long, long ago, but didn\'t colonize further due to the 3-parsec
gap in all other direction (that was before I got hold of the Foreven
Map. There\'s a world two parsecs from Andor there, but I ruthlessly
destroyed it when I noticed it). Anyway, the Droyne explored a bit in
special scout ships, but eventually decided to stick to Candory and
leave the rest of the galaxy alone. They were found by Imperial scouts
late in the 1st Century. No interdict, since they were star-travelling
(albeit in a small way) already. In 610 they became an Imperial protectorate
when the Imperium established Districts 267 (later Five Sisters), 268,
269 (Egyrn), 270 (Pax Rulin), 271 (Sindal), 272 (Tobia), and 273 (Usher).
In 810 they were interdicted without explanation to the public (The
subsector governor discovered they were psionic? Ancient sites were
discovered on Andor?). However, since the locals were already Imperial
clients they have the right to come and go as they please. Hence Droyne
ships from Andor plying the spacelanes with impunity.

Imperial scientists have been known to obtain permission to visit Andor
and Candory on those extremely rare occasions where the Droyne have
invited them to examine an Ancient site.


