    'topic' => 'missile long distance fire',
    'body' => 'Peter L. Berghold was wandering about standard fleet practice in Traveller.
I am using MT rules with vector movement and slightly different sensor rules,
but I suspect that everything I say should apply to standard Mt as well.

It looks like that in MT it is easier to destroy your opponent than to 
see him (not too unreasonable after all..). As a result in my battles 
each opponent tends to stay at a safe distance (out of sensor range) from 
the enemy fleet, trying to guide its battleships fire (mesons and missiles)
using AWACS ships. Part of the battle preparation is trying to locate the 
enemy\'s AWACS..

I suspect that many others are using picket ships of some sort..

  Cheers, Max


