That Andor and Candory. Andor was spelled with a y in one of the earliest
publications, but all (most?) other sources leave it out. No official
explanation for the interdict has been published, but note the curious 
fact that they have functioning starports despite being interdicted.
Also I think we\'ve seen Droyne ships (in _Merchant Prince_?) that are
registered to Andor mucking about the Marches.

In my universe.................
...................... However, since the locals were already Imperial
clients they have the right to come and go as they please. Hence Droyne
ships from Andor plying the spacelanes with impunity.

Imperial scientists have been known to obtain permission to visit Andor
and Candory on those extremely rare occasions where the Droyne have
invited them to examine an Ancient site.


