    'body' => '
Hello there.

Well, I would have to agree that missiles are difficult to redesign with 
the rules at present.  What you need is a copy of Special Supplement 3, 
Missiles in Traveller, which was included in JTAS #21.  Although, this 
makes things only a little clearer.

I have not been able to reproduce the MT standard ship missile with this 
system, and according to its rules, the Nuclear and Antimatter missiles 
would not be able to be fired from a missile turret.  This has to do with 
ships missiles being packaged in special missile tubes that hold the 
missiles right up until firing.  They are actually fired in these standard
"shipping/launch container" packages, which hold 50kg of missile, which 
is the way in which missile construction is based, on weight.  As Nuclear 
and Antimatter missiles are 70kg and 90kg respectively, they will not fit 
in a standard shipping container and cannot be fired from a standard 
missile turret\'s launch rails.

In this supplement, I have also found major typos in the construction 
formulae versus the written rules.  So I have adopted the use of the 
written rules.  Antimatter missiles do not exist in this supplement, but 
Fusion warheads do, as do Enhanced Radiation.  It also contains three 
types of solid fuel propulsion systems which allow any propulsion rating 
you want with the necessary rules.  You wanna 6G6?  Sure, no prob.  OH, 
BTW, that is 6 1200 second rounds.

My advice to you all is to fix the rules with major infusions of 
Striker.  There is some neat stuff in this supplement, but it is for 
Classic Trav, not Mega.

I myself have always liked the Star Trek torpedo concept, so I have been 
modifying the rules to generate bigger missiles, if need be.

	Ciao,
	Anthony


