    'body' => 'In XBOAT Digest 329+, Anthony Neal et al replied about missiles.

One thing I found with Mayday was that firing 6G missiles after
fleeing 6G ships is pointless - they will never catch up.

On round 1, the missile has a vector of 6 hexes + the firing
ship\'s vector. On subsequent rounds, it will only increase
this by 6 hexes - just what the enemy ship is doing.

Against slower ships, they may catch up... but will probably
run out of fuel first.

..This may be another argument for x-ray laser detonation
missiles (wash your mouth out!), or: FASTER MISSILES!

I found it is possible to create a STANDARD missile which is
capable of 10G, and then created military missiles capable of
21G! Combat in Mayday becomes easier and more like HG - missiles
hit in the turn they are fired, so no before-during-after vector
counters are necessary.

These missiles were turret-capable. I will try to dig out my
old designs, but I am not promising anything - I think they are
at the bottom of the pile.

