For my two cents worth on the subject, I think that the skill TACTICS allows
the experienced person to set up a "killing field" and respond to situations
of surprise when they find themselves in a firefight.  The skill TACTICS in
my campaign does not always outdo someone with high dexterity: it all
depends on the situation.

If what you have is two guys in a street drawing down on each other in
gunslinger fashion, there really isn\'t much INHO that the skill of TACTICS
will add to my defense.  If I am in that situation, I want to be the quicker
of the two, with the steadiest aim and the best luck, not a sound strategist
or tactician.

However, if you will give me time to assess the situation and use my TACTICS
skill to evaluate the situation aforehand I am going to find that sucker
from 500-600 meters w/my ranged in rifle and do them in, lay an ambush to
them on the way to the street or whatever, using in best fashion all of the
resources available to me at that time.

There is a lot to be said for TACTICS and DEX, but the situation should rule
and as always the GM is the final arbiter.

